{"type":"USJ","version":"3.1","content":[{"type":"book","marker":"id","code":"JER","content":["- Berean Study Bible"]},{"type":"para","marker":"h","content":["Jeremiah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc1","content":["Jeremiah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc2","content":["Jeremiah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc3","content":["Jeremiah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt1","content":["Jeremiah"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"1"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Call of Jeremiah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"These are the words of Jeremiah son of Hilkiah, one of the priests in Anathoth in the territory of Benjamin."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"The word of the LORD came to Jeremiah in the thirteenth year of the reign of Josiah son of Amon king of Judah,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"and through the days of Jehoiakim son of Josiah king of Judah, until the fifth month of the eleventh year of Zedekiah son of Josiah king of Judah, when the people of Jerusalem went into exile."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"The word of the LORD came to me, saying:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"“Before I formed you in the womb I knew you,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and before you were born I set you apart"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and appointed you as a prophet to the nations.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"“Ah, Lord GOD,” I said, “I surely do not know how to speak, for I am only a child!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"But the LORD told me:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Do not say,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘I am only a child.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For to everyone I send you,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["you must go,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and all that I command you,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["you must speak."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Do not be afraid of them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for I am with you to deliver you,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Then the LORD reached out His hand, touched my mouth, and said to me:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Behold, I have put My words"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in your mouth."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"See, I have appointed you today"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["over nations and kingdoms"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["to uproot and tear down,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to destroy and overthrow,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to build and plant.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"And the word of the LORD came to me, asking, “Jeremiah, what do you see?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“I see a branch of an almond tree,” I replied."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"“You have observed correctly,” said the LORD, “for I am watching",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:12"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["The Hebrew for ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["watching"]}," sounds like the Hebrew for ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["almond tree"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"over My word to accomplish it.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Again the word of the LORD came to me, asking, “What do you see?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“I see a boiling pot,” I replied, “and it is tilting toward us from the north.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Then the LORD said to me, “Disaster from the north will be poured out on all who live in the land.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"For I am about to summon all the clans and kingdoms of the north,” declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Their kings will come and set up their thrones"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["at the entrance of the gates of Jerusalem."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They will attack all her surrounding walls"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and all the other cities of Judah."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"I will pronounce My judgments against them"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for all their wickedness,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["because they have forsaken Me,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they have burned incense to other gods"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and worshiped the works of their own hands."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Get yourself ready.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:17"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Gird up your loins."]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"Stand up and tell them everything that I command you. Do not be intimidated by them, or I will terrify you before them.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Now behold, this day I have made you like a fortified city, an iron pillar, and bronze walls against the whole land—against the kings of Judah, its officials, its priests, and the people of the land.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"They will fight against you but will never overcome you, since I am with you to deliver you,” declares the LORD."]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"2"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Israel Has Forsaken God"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Now the word of the LORD came to me, saying,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"“Go and proclaim in the hearing of Jerusalem that this is what the LORD says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘I remember the devotion of your youth,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["your love as a bride,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["how you followed Me in the wilderness,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in a land not sown."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Israel was holy to the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the firstfruits of His harvest."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["All who devoured her"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["were found guilty;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["disaster came upon them,’”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Hear the word of the LORD, O house of Jacob, and all you families of the house of Israel.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"This is what the LORD says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“What fault did your fathers find in Me"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that they strayed so far from Me?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They followed worthless idols,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and became worthless themselves."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"They did not ask, ‘Where is the LORD"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["who brought us up from the land of Egypt,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["who led us through the wilderness,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["through a land of deserts and pits,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["a land of drought and darkness,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a land where no one travels and no one lives?’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"I brought you into a fertile land"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to eat its fruit and bounty,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["but you came and defiled My land"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and made My inheritance detestable."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"The priests did not ask,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘Where is the LORD?’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The experts in the law no longer knew Me,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the leaders rebelled against Me."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The prophets prophesied by Baal"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and followed useless idols."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Therefore, I will contend with you again,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["And I will bring a case"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["against your children’s children."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Cross over to the coasts of Cyprus",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:10"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Kittim"]},""]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and take a look;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["send to Kedar and consider carefully;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["see if there has ever been anything like this:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Has a nation ever changed its gods?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["(Yet they are not gods at all.)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["But My people have exchanged their Glory",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:11"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["their glorious God"]},""]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for useless idols."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Be stunned by this, O heavens;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["be shocked and utterly appalled,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"“For My people have committed two evils:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They have forsaken Me,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the fountain of living water,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and they have dug their own cisterns—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["broken cisterns that cannot hold water."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Consequence of Israel’s Sin"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Is Israel a slave?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Was he born into slavery?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Why then has he become prey?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"The young lions have roared at him;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they have sounded their voices."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They have laid waste his land;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["his cities lie in ruins, without inhabitant."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"The men of Memphis",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:16"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["LXX; Hebrew ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Noph"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"and Tahpanhes"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["have shaved the crown of your head."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Have you not brought this on yourself"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["by forsaking the LORD your God"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["when He led you in the way?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Now what will you gain on your way to Egypt"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to drink the waters of the Nile",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:18"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["of Shihor"]},", a branch of the Nile River"]}],"caller":"+"},"?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["What will you gain on your way to Assyria"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to drink the waters of the Euphrates",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:18"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["the River"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Your own evil will discipline you;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["your own apostasies will reprimand you."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Consider and realize"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["how evil and bitter it is"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for you to forsake the LORD your God"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and to have no fear of Me,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the Lord GOD of Hosts."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"“For long ago you broke your yoke"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and tore off your chains,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["saying, ‘I will not serve!’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Indeed, on every high hill"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and under every green tree"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["you lay down as a prostitute."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"I had planted you like a choice vine"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from the very best seed."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["How could you turn yourself before Me"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["into a rotten, wild vine?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Although you wash with lye"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and use an abundance of soap,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["the stain of your guilt"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["is still before Me,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the Lord GOD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Israel’s Unfaithfulness"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Judges 2:10–15; Isaiah 43:22–28)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"“How can you say, ‘I am not defiled;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I have not run after the Baals’?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Look at your behavior in the valley;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["acknowledge what you have done."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["You are a swift young she-camel"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["galloping here and there,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"a wild donkey at home in the wilderness,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["sniffing the wind in the heat of her desire."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Who can restrain her passion?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["All who seek her need not weary themselves;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in mating season they will find her."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"You should have kept your feet from going bare"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and your throat from being thirsty."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["But you said, ‘It is hopeless!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["For I love foreign gods,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and I must go after them.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"As the thief is ashamed when he is caught,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["so the house of Israel is disgraced."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They, their kings, their officials,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["their priests, and their prophets"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"say to a tree, ‘You are my father,’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and to a stone, ‘You gave me birth.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They have turned their backs to Me"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and not their faces."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Yet in the time of trouble, they say,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘Rise up and save us!’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"But where are the gods you made for yourselves?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Let them rise up in your time of trouble"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and save you if they can;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for your gods are as numerous"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["as your cities, O Judah."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"Why do you bring a case against Me?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You have all rebelled against Me,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"“I have struck your sons in vain;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they accepted no discipline."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Your own sword has devoured your prophets"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like a voracious lion.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"You people of this generation, consider the word of the LORD:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Have I been a wilderness to Israel"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["or a land of dense darkness?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Why do My people say,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘We are free to roam;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["we will come to You no more’?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"Does a maiden forget her jewelry"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["or a bride her wedding sash?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Yet My people have forgotten Me"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for days without number."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"How skillfully you pursue love!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Even the most immoral of women"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["could learn from your ways."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"Moreover, your skirts are stained"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with the blood of the innocent poor,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["though you did not find them breaking in."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["But in spite of all these things"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"you say, ‘I am innocent."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Surely His anger will turn from me.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Behold, I will judge you,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because you say, ‘I have not sinned.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"How impulsive you are,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["constantly changing your ways!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["You will be disappointed by Egypt"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["just as you were by Assyria."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"Moreover, you will leave that place"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with your hands on your head,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for the LORD has rejected those you trust;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["you will not prosper by their help.”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"3"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Wages of the Harlot"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"“If a man divorces his wife"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and she leaves him to marry another,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["can he ever return to her?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Would not such a land be completely defiled?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["But you have played the harlot with many lovers—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and you would return to Me?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"“Lift up your eyes to the barren heights and see."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Is there any place where you have not been violated?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["You sat beside the highways waiting for your lovers,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like a nomad in the desert."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["You have defiled the land"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with your prostitution and wickedness."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Therefore the showers have been withheld,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and no spring rains have fallen."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Yet you have the brazen look of a prostitute;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["you refuse to be ashamed."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Have you not just called to Me,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘My Father, You are my friend from youth."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Will He be angry forever?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Will He be indignant to the end?’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["This you have spoken,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but you keep doing all the evil you can.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Judah Follows Israel’s Example"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Now in the days of King Josiah, the LORD said to me, “Have you seen what faithless Israel has done? She has gone up on every high hill and under every green tree to prostitute herself there.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"I thought that after she had done all these things, she would return to Me. But she did not return, and her unfaithful sister Judah saw it."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"She saw",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:8"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["DSS, one LXX manuscript, and Syriac; MT ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["I saw"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"that because faithless Israel had committed adultery, I gave her a certificate of divorce and sent her away. Yet that unfaithful sister Judah had no fear and prostituted herself as well.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Indifferent to her own infidelity, Israel had defiled the land and committed adultery with stones and trees.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Yet in spite of all this, her unfaithful sister Judah did not return to Me with all her heart, but only in pretense,” declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["A Call to Repentance"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Hosea 14:1–3; Zechariah 1:1–6)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"And the LORD said to me, “Faithless Israel has shown herself more righteous than unfaithful Judah.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Go, proclaim this message toward the north:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘Return, O faithless Israel,’ declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘I will no longer look on you with anger,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for I am merciful,’ declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘I will not be angry forever."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Only acknowledge your guilt,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that you have rebelled against the LORD your God."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["You have scattered your favors to foreign gods"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["under every green tree"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and have not obeyed My voice,’”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"“Return, O faithless children,” declares the LORD, “for I am your master, and I will take you—one from a city and two from a family—and bring you to Zion.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Then I will give you shepherds after My own heart, who will feed you with knowledge and understanding.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"“In those days, when you multiply and increase in the land,” declares the LORD, “they will no longer discuss the ark of the covenant of the LORD. It will never come to mind, and no one will remember it or miss it, nor will another one be made."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"At that time they will call Jerusalem The Throne of the LORD, and all the nations will be gathered in Jerusalem to honor the name of the LORD. They will no longer follow the stubbornness of their evil hearts.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"In those days the house of Judah will walk with the house of Israel, and they will come together from the land of the north to the land that I gave to your fathers as an inheritance."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Then I said, ‘How I long to make you My sons"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and give you a desirable land,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["the most beautiful inheritance"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["of all the nations!’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I thought you would call Me ‘Father’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and never turn away from following Me."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"But as a woman may betray her husband,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["so you have betrayed Me, O house of Israel,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"A voice is heard on the barren heights,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the children of Israel weeping and begging for mercy,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["because they have perverted their ways"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and forgotten the LORD their God."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"“Return, O faithless children,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and I will heal your faithlessness.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Here we are. We come to You,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for You are the LORD our God."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Surely deception comes from the hills,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and commotion from the mountains."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Surely the salvation of Israel"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["is in the LORD our God."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"From our youth, that shameful god"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["has consumed what our fathers have worked for—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["their flocks and herds,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["their sons and daughters."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"Let us lie down in our shame;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["let our disgrace cover us."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["We have sinned against the LORD our God,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["both we and our fathers;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["from our youth even to this day"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["we have not obeyed the voice of the LORD our God.”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"4"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["A Plea to Return"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"“If you will return, O Israel,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["return to Me,” declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“If you will remove your detestable idols from My sight"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and no longer waver,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"and if you can swear, ‘As surely as the LORD lives,’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in truth, in justice, and in righteousness,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["then the nations will be blessed by Him,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and in Him they will glory.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"For this is what the LORD says to the men of Judah and Jerusalem:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Break up your unplowed ground,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and do not sow among the thorns."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Circumcise yourselves to the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and remove the foreskins of your hearts,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["O men of Judah and people of Jerusalem."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Otherwise, My wrath will break out like fire"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and burn with no one to extinguish it,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because of your evil deeds.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Disaster from the North"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Announce in Judah, proclaim in Jerusalem, and say:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Blow the ram’s horn throughout the land."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Cry aloud and say,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘Assemble yourselves"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and let us flee to the fortified cities.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Raise a signal flag toward Zion."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Seek refuge! Do not delay!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For I am bringing disaster from the north,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and terrible destruction."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"A lion has gone up from his thicket,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and a destroyer of nations has set out."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["He has left his lair"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to lay waste your land."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Your cities will be reduced to ruins"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and lie uninhabited."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"So put on sackcloth,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["mourn and wail,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for the fierce anger of the LORD"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["has not turned away from us.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"“In that day,” declares the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“the king and officials will lose their courage."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The priests will tremble in fear,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the prophets will be astounded.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Then I said, “Ah, Lord GOD, how completely You have deceived this people and Jerusalem by saying, ‘You will have peace,’ while a sword is at our throats.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"At that time it will be said to this people and to Jerusalem, “A searing wind from the barren heights in the desert blows toward the daughter of My people, but not to winnow or to sift;",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"a wind too strong for that comes from Me. Now I also pronounce judgments against them.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Behold, he advances like the clouds,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["his chariots like the whirlwind."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["His horses are swifter than eagles."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Woe to us, for we are ruined!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Wash the evil from your heart, O Jerusalem,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["so that you may be saved."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["How long will you harbor"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["wicked thoughts within you?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"For a voice resounds from Dan,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["proclaiming disaster from the hills of Ephraim."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Warn the nations now!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Proclaim to Jerusalem:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“A besieging army comes from a distant land;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they raise their voices against the cities of Judah."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"They surround her like men guarding a field,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because she has rebelled against Me,” declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"“Your ways and deeds"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["have brought this upon you."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["This is your punishment; how bitter it is,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because it pierces to the heart!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Lamentation for Judah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"My anguish, my anguish! I writhe in pain!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Oh, the pain in my chest!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["My heart pounds within me;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I cannot be silent."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For I have heard the sound of the horn,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the alarm of battle."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Disaster after disaster is proclaimed,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the whole land is laid waste."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["My tents are destroyed in an instant,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["my curtains in a moment."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"How long must I see the signal flag"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and hear the sound of the horn?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"“For My people are fools;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they have not known Me."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They are foolish children,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["without understanding."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They are skilled in doing evil,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but they know not how to do good.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"I looked at the earth,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and it was formless and void;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I looked to the heavens,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they had no light."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"I looked at the mountains,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and behold, they were quaking;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["all the hills were swaying."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"I looked, and no man was left;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["all the birds of the air had fled."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"I looked, and the fruitful land was a desert."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["All its cities were torn down"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["before the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["before His fierce anger."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"For this is what the LORD says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“The whole land will be desolate,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but I will not finish its destruction."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"Therefore the earth will mourn"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the heavens above will grow dark."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I have spoken, I have planned,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and I will not relent or turn back.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"Every city flees"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["at the sound of the horseman and archer."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They enter the thickets"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and climb among the rocks."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Every city is abandoned;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["no inhabitant is left."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"And you, O devastated one, what will you do,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["though you dress yourself in scarlet,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["though you adorn yourself with gold jewelry,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["though you enlarge your eyes with paint?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["You adorn yourself in vain; your lovers despise you;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they want to take your life."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"For I hear a cry like a woman in labor,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a cry of anguish like one bearing her first child—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["the cry of the Daughter of Zion gasping for breath,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["stretching out her hands to say,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Woe is me,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for my soul faints before the murderers!”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"5"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["No One Is Just"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"“Go up and down the streets of Jerusalem."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Look now and take note; search her squares."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["If you can find a single person,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["anyone who acts justly,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["anyone who seeks the truth,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["then I will forgive the city."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"Although they say, ‘As surely as the LORD lives,’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they are swearing falsely.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"O LORD, do not Your eyes look for truth?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You struck them, but they felt no pain."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["You finished them off,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but they refused to accept discipline."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They have made their faces harder than stone"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and refused to repent."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Then I said, “They are only the poor;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they have played the fool,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for they do not know the way of the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the justice of their God."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"I will go to the powerful"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and speak to them."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Surely they know the way of the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the justice of their God.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["But they too, with one accord, had broken the yoke"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and torn off the chains."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Therefore a lion from the forest will strike them down,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a wolf from the desert will ravage them."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["A leopard will lie in wait near their cities,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and everyone who ventures out will be torn to pieces."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For their rebellious acts are many,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and their unfaithful deeds are numerous."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"“Why should I forgive you?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Your children have forsaken Me"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and sworn by gods that are not gods."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I satisfied their needs, yet they committed adultery"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and assembled at the houses of prostitutes."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"They are well-fed, lusty stallions,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["each neighing after his neighbor’s wife."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Should I not punish them for these things?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Should I not avenge Myself"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["on such a nation as this?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Go up through her vineyards and ravage them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but do not finish them off."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Strip off her branches,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for they do not belong to the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"For the house of Israel and the house of Judah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["have been utterly unfaithful to Me,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"They have lied about the LORD and said:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“He will not do anything; harm will not come to us;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["we will not see sword or famine."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"The prophets are but wind,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the word is not in them."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["So let their own predictions befall them.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:13"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["let this befall them."]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Judgment Proclaimed"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Therefore this is what the LORD God of Hosts says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Because you have spoken this word,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will make My words a fire in your mouth"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and this people the wood it consumes."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Behold, I am bringing a distant nation against you,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["O house of Israel,” declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“It is an established nation,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["an ancient nation,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["a nation whose language you do not know"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and whose speech you do not understand."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Their quivers are like open graves;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they are all mighty men."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"They will devour your harvest and food;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they will consume your sons and daughters;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["they will eat up your flocks and herds;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they will feed on your vines and fig trees."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["With the sword they will destroy"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the fortified cities in which you trust.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"“Yet even in those days,” declares the LORD, “I will not make a full end of you.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"And when the people ask, ‘For what offense has the LORD our God done all these things to us?’ You are to tell them, ‘Just as you have forsaken Me and served foreign gods in your land, so will you serve foreigners in a land that is not your own.’”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Declare this in the house of Jacob and proclaim it in Judah:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"“Hear this,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["O foolish and senseless people,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["who have eyes but do not see,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["who have ears but do not hear."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Do you not fear Me?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Do you not tremble before Me,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the One who set the sand as the boundary for the sea,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["an enduring barrier it cannot cross?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The waves surge, but they cannot prevail."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They roar but cannot cross it."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"But these people have stubborn and rebellious hearts."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They have turned aside and gone away."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"They have not said in their hearts,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘Let us fear the LORD our God,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["who gives the rains, both autumn and spring, in season,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["who keeps for us the appointed weeks of harvest.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"Your iniquities have diverted these from you;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["your sins have deprived you of My bounty."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"For among My people are wicked men;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they watch like fowlers lying in wait;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they set a trap to catch men."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"Like cages full of birds,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["so their houses are full of deceit."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Therefore they have become powerful and rich."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"They have grown fat and sleek,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and have excelled in the deeds of the wicked."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They have not taken up the cause of the fatherless,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that they might prosper;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["nor have they defended"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the rights of the needy."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"Should I not punish them for these things?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Should I not avenge Myself"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["on such a nation as this?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"A horrible and shocking thing"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["has happened in the land."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"The prophets prophesy falsely,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the priests rule by their own authority."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["My people love it so,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but what will you do in the end?.’’]"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"6"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jerusalem’s Final Warning"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"“Run for cover, O sons of Benjamin;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["flee from Jerusalem!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Sound the ram’s horn in Tekoa;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["send up a signal over Beth-haccherem,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for disaster looms from the north,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["even great destruction."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"Though she is beautiful and delicate,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will destroy the Daughter of Zion.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:2"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["To a lovely and delicate woman I have likened the Daughter of Zion"]},""]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Shepherds and their flocks"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["will come against her;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["they will pitch their tents all around her,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["each tending his own portion:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"‘Prepare for battle against her;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["rise up, let us attack at noon."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Woe to us, for the daylight is fading;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the evening shadows grow long."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Rise up, let us attack by night"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and destroy her fortresses!’”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"For this is what the LORD of Hosts says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Cut down the trees"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and raise a siege ramp against Jerusalem."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["This city must be punished;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["there is nothing but oppression in her midst."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"As a well gushes its water,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["so she pours out her evil."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Violence and destruction resound in her;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["sickness and wounds are ever before Me."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Be forewarned, O Jerusalem,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["or I will turn away from you;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will make you a desolation,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a land without inhabitant.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"This is what the LORD of Hosts says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Glean the remnant of Israel"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["as thoroughly as a vine."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Pass your hand once more like a grape gatherer"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["over the branches.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"To whom can I give this warning?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Who will listen to me?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Look, their ears are closed,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:10"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["uncircumcised"]},""]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["so they cannot hear."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["See, the word of the LORD has become offensive to them;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they find no pleasure in it."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"But I am full of the LORD’s wrath;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I am tired of holding it back."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Pour it out on the children in the street,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and on the young men gathered together."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For both husband and wife will be captured,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the old and the very old alike."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Their houses will be turned over to others,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["their fields and wives as well,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for I will stretch out My hand"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["against the inhabitants of the land,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"“For from the least of them to the greatest,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["all are greedy for gain;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["from prophet to priest,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["all practice deceit."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"They dress the wound of My people"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with very little care,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["saying, ‘Peace, peace,’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["when there is no peace at all."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Are they ashamed of the abomination they have committed?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["No, they have no shame at all;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they do not even know how to blush."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["So they will fall among the fallen;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["when I punish them, they will collapse,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["says the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"This is what the LORD says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Stand at the crossroads and look."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Ask for the ancient paths: ‘Where is the good way?’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Then walk in it, and you will find rest for your souls."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["But they said, ‘We will not walk in it!’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"I appointed watchmen over you and said,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘Listen for the sound of the ram’s horn.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["But they answered, ‘We will not listen!’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Therefore hear, O nations,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and learn, O congregations,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["what will happen to them."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Hear, O earth! I am bringing disaster on this people,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the fruit of their own schemes,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["because they have paid no attention to My word"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and have rejected My instruction."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"What use to Me is frankincense from Sheba"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["or sweet cane from a distant land?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Your burnt offerings are not acceptable;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["your sacrifices do not please Me.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Therefore this is what the LORD says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“I will lay stumbling blocks before this people;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["fathers and sons alike will be staggered;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["friends and neighbors will perish.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["An Invasion from the North"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"This is what the LORD says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Behold, an army is coming"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from the land of the north;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["a great nation is stirred up"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from the ends of the earth."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"They grasp the bow and spear;",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:23"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["javelin"]},""]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they are cruel and merciless."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Their voice roars like the sea,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they ride upon horses,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["lined up like men in formation"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["against you, O Daughter of Zion.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"We have heard the report;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["our hands hang limp."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Anguish has gripped us,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["pain like that of a woman in labor."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"Do not go out to the fields;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["do not walk the road."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For the enemy has a sword;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["terror is on every side."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"O daughter of my people,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["dress yourselves in sackcloth and roll in ashes."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Mourn with bitter wailing,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["as you would for an only son,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for suddenly the destroyer"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["will come upon us."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"“I have appointed you to examine My people like ore,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:27"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["to examine My people, a fortress"]},""]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["so you may know and try their ways."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"All are hardened rebels,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["walking around as slanderers."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They are bronze and iron;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["all of them are corrupt."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"The bellows blow fiercely,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["blasting away the lead with fire."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The refining proceeds in vain,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the wicked are not purged."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"They are called rejected silver,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because the LORD has rejected them.”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"7"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jeremiah’s Message at the Temple Gate"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"This is the word that came to Jeremiah from the LORD, saying,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"“Stand in the gate of the house of the LORD and proclaim this message: Hear the word of the LORD, all you people of Judah who enter through these gates to worship the LORD.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Thus says the LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel: Correct your ways and deeds, and I will let you live in this place.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Do not trust in deceptive words, saying:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘This is the temple of the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the temple of the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the temple of the LORD.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"For if you really correct your ways and deeds, if you act justly toward one another,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"if you no longer oppress the foreigner and the fatherless and the widow, and if you no longer shed innocent blood in this place or follow other gods to your own harm,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"then I will let you live in this place, in the land that I gave to your fathers forever and ever."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"But look, you keep trusting in deceptive words to no avail.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Will you steal and murder, commit adultery and perjury, burn incense to Baal, and follow other gods that you have not known,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"and then come and stand before Me in this house, which bears My Name, and say, ‘We are delivered, so we can continue with all these abominations’?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Has this house, which bears My Name, become a den of robbers",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:11"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Cited in",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Matthew 21:13"]},",",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Mark 11:17"]},", and",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Luke 19:46"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"in your sight? Yes, I too have seen it, declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"But go now to the place in Shiloh where I first made a dwelling for My Name, and see what I did to it because of the wickedness of My people Israel.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"And now, because you have done all these things, declares the LORD, and because I have spoken to you again and again",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:13"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["I have spoken to you, rising up early and speaking,"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"but you would not listen, and I have called to you but you would not answer,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"therefore what I did to Shiloh I will now do to the house that bears My Name, the house in which you trust, the place that I gave to you and your fathers.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"And I will cast you out of My presence, just as I have cast out all your brothers, all the descendants of Ephraim."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Judah’s Idolatry Persists"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"As for you, do not pray for these people, do not offer a plea or petition on their behalf, and do not beg Me, for I will not listen to you.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Do you not see what they are doing in the cities of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"The sons gather wood, the fathers light the fire, and the women knead the dough to make cakes for the Queen of Heaven; they pour out drink offerings to other gods to provoke Me to anger.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"But am I the One they are provoking? declares the LORD. Is it not themselves they spite, to their own shame?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Therefore this is what the Lord GOD says: Behold, My anger and My fury will be poured out on this place, on man and beast, on the trees of the field and the produce of the land, and it will burn and not be extinguished."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"This is what the LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel, says: Add your burnt offerings to your other sacrifices and eat the meat yourselves!",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"For when I brought your fathers out of the land of Egypt, I did not merely command them about burnt offerings and sacrifices,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"but this is what I commanded them: Obey Me, and I will be your God, and you will be My people. You must walk in all the ways I have commanded you, so that it may go well with you."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Yet they did not listen or incline their ear, but they followed the stubborn inclinations of their own evil hearts. They went backward and not forward.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"From the day your fathers came out of the land of Egypt until this day, I have sent you all My servants the prophets again and again.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:25"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["I have sent you all My servants the prophets daily, rising up early and sending (them)."]},""]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"Yet they would not listen to Me or incline their ear, but they stiffened their necks and did more evil than their fathers."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"When you tell them all these things, they will not listen to you. When you call to them, they will not answer.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"Therefore you must say to them, ‘This is the nation that would not listen to the voice of the LORD their God and would not receive correction. Truth has perished; it has disappeared from their lips.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"Cut off your hair and throw it away. Raise up a lamentation on the barren heights, for the LORD has rejected and forsaken the generation of His wrath.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Valley of Slaughter"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"For the people of Judah have done evil in My sight, declares the LORD. They have set up their abominations in the house that bears My Name, and so have defiled it.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"They have built the high places of Topheth in the Valley of Ben-hinnom so they could burn their sons and daughters in the fire—something I never commanded, nor did it even enter My mind."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"So behold, the days are coming, declares the LORD, when this place will no longer be called Topheth and the Valley of Ben-hinnom, but the Valley of Slaughter. For they will bury the dead in Topheth until there is no more room.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"The corpses of this people will become food for the birds of the air and the beasts of the earth, and there will be no one to scare them away."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"I will remove from the cities of Judah and the streets of Jerusalem the sounds of joy and gladness and the voices of the bride and bridegroom, for the land will become a wasteland.”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"8"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Judah’s Sin and Punishment"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"“At that time,” declares the LORD, “the bones of the kings of Judah, the bones of the officials, the bones of the priests, the bones of the prophets, and the bones of the people of Jerusalem will be removed from their graves.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"They will be exposed to the sun and moon, and to all the host of heaven which they have loved, served, followed, consulted, and worshiped. Their bones will not be gathered up or buried, but will become like dung lying on the ground.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"And wherever I have banished them, the remnant of this evil family will choose death over life,” declares the LORD of Hosts."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"So you are to tell them this is what the LORD says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Do men fall and not get up again?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Does one turn away and not return?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Why then have these people turned away?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Why does Jerusalem always turn away?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They cling to deceit;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they refuse to return."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"I have listened and heard;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they do not speak what is right."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["No one repents of his wickedness,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["asking, ‘What have I done?’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Everyone has pursued his own course"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like a horse charging into battle."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Even the stork in the sky"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["knows her appointed seasons."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The turtledove, the swift, and the thrush",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:7"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["The precise identification of some of these birds is uncertain."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["keep their time of migration,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["but My people do not know"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the requirements of the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"How can you say, ‘We are wise,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the Law of the LORD is with us,’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["when in fact the lying pen of the scribes"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["has produced a deception?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"The wise will be put to shame;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they will be dismayed and trapped."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Since they have rejected the word of the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["what wisdom do they really have?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Therefore I will give their wives to other men"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and their fields to new owners."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For from the least of them to the greatest,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["all are greedy for gain;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["from prophet to priest,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["all practice deceit."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"They dress the wound of the daughter of My people"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with very little care,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["saying, ‘Peace, peace,’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["when there is no peace at all."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Are they ashamed of the abomination they have committed?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["No, they have no shame at all;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they do not even know how to blush."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["So they will fall among the fallen;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["when I punish them, they will collapse,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["says the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"I will take away their harvest,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["There will be no grapes on the vine,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["nor figs on the tree,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and even the leaf will wither."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Whatever I have given them will be lost to them.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The People Respond"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Why are we just sitting here?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Gather together,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["let us flee to the fortified cities and perish there,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the LORD our God has doomed us."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["He has given us poisoned water to drink,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because we have sinned against the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"We hoped for peace,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but no good has come,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for a time of healing,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but there was only terror."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"The snorting of enemy horses"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["is heard from Dan."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["At the sound of the neighing of mighty steeds,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the whole land quakes."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They come to devour the land and everything in it,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the city and all who dwell in it."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"“For behold, I will send snakes among you,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["vipers that cannot be charmed,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they will bite you,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jeremiah Weeps for His People"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"My sorrow is beyond healing;",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:18"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["O my Comforter in sorrow,"]},""]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["my heart is faint within me."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Listen to the cry of the daughter of my people"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from a land far away:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Is the LORD no longer in Zion?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Is her King no longer there?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Why have they provoked Me to anger"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with their carved images,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with their worthless foreign idols?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"“The harvest has passed, the summer has ended,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but we have not been saved.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"For the brokenness of the daughter of my people I am crushed."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I mourn; horror has gripped me."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Is there no balm in Gilead?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Is no physician there?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Why then has the health of the daughter of my people"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["not been restored?"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"9"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["A Lament over Zion"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Oh, that my head were a spring of water,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and my eyes a fountain of tears!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I would weep day and night"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["over the slain daughter of my people."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"If only I had a traveler’s lodge in the wilderness,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I would abandon my people and depart from them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for they are all adulterers,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a crowd of faithless people."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"“They bend their tongues like bows;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["lies prevail over truth in the land."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For they proceed from evil to evil,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they do not take Me into account,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"“Let everyone guard against his neighbor;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["do not trust any brother,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for every brother deals craftily,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and every friend spreads slander."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Each one betrays his friend;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["no one tells the truth."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They have taught their tongues to lie;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they wear themselves out committing iniquity."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"You dwell",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:6"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, Jeremiah dwells (the Hebrew is singular)"]}],"caller":"+"},"in the midst of deception;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in their deceit they refuse to know Me,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Therefore this is what the LORD of Hosts says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Behold, I will refine them and test them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for what else can I do"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because of",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:7"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["LXX ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["because of the wickedness of"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"the daughter of My people?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Their tongues are deadly arrows;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they speak deception."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["With his mouth a man speaks peace to his neighbor,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but in his heart he sets a trap for him."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Should I not punish them for these things?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Should I not avenge Myself"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["on such a nation as this?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"I will take up a weeping and wailing for the mountains,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a dirge over the wilderness pasture,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for they have been scorched so no one passes through,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the lowing of cattle is not heard."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Both the birds of the air and the beasts have fled;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they have gone away."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"“And I will make Jerusalem a heap of rubble,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a haunt for jackals;",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:11"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["serpents"]}," or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["dragons"]},""]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and I will make the cities of Judah a desolation,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["without inhabitant.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Who is the man wise enough to understand this? To whom has the mouth of the LORD spoken, that he may explain it? Why is the land destroyed and scorched like a desert, so no one can pass through it?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"And the LORD answered, “It is because they have forsaken My law, which I set before them; they have not walked in it or obeyed My voice.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Instead, they have followed the stubbornness of their hearts and gone after the Baals, as their fathers taught them.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Therefore this is what the LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel, says: “Behold, I will feed this people wormwood and give them poisoned water to drink.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"I will scatter them among the nations that neither they nor their fathers have known, and I will send a sword after them until I have finished them off.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"This is what the LORD of Hosts says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Take note, and summon the wailing women;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["send for the most skillful among them."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Let them come quickly"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and take up a lament over us,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["that our eyes may overflow with tears,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and our eyelids may gush with water."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"For the sound of wailing"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["is heard from Zion:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘How devastated we are!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["How great is our shame!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For we have abandoned the land"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because our dwellings have been torn down.’”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Now, O women, hear the word of the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Open your ears to the word of His mouth."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Teach your daughters to wail,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and one another to lament."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"For death has climbed in through our windows;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["it has entered our fortresses"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["to cut off the children from the streets,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the young men from the town squares."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Declare that this is what the LORD says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“The corpses of men will fall like dung"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["upon the open field,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["like newly cut grain behind the reaper,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with no one to gather it.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"This is what the LORD says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Let not the wise man boast in his wisdom,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["nor the strong man in his strength,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["nor the wealthy man in his riches."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"But let him who boasts boast in this,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that he understands and knows Me,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["that I am the LORD,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:24"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Cited in",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["1 Corinthians 1:31"]},"and",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["2 Corinthians 10:17"]}]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["who exercises loving devotion,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:24"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Forms of the Hebrew ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["chesed"]}," are translated here and in most cases throughout the Scriptures as ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["loving devotion"]},"; the range of meaning includes ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["love"]},", ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["goodness"]},", ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["kindness"]},", ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["faithfulness"]},", and ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["mercy"]},", as well as ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["loyalty to a covenant"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["justice and righteousness on the earth—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for I delight in these things,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"“Behold, the days are coming,” declares the LORD, “when I will punish all who are circumcised only in the flesh—",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"Egypt, Judah, Edom, Ammon, Moab, and all the inhabitants of the desert who clip the hair of their temples. For all these nations are uncircumcised, and the whole house of Israel is uncircumcised in heart.”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"10"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Sovereignty of God"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Hear the word that the LORD speaks to you, O house of Israel.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"This is what the LORD says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Do not learn the ways of the nations"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["or be terrified by the signs in the heavens,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["though the nations themselves are terrified by them."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"For the customs of the peoples are worthless;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they cut down a tree from the forest;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["it is shaped with a chisel"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["by the hands of a craftsman."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"They adorn it with silver and gold"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and fasten it with hammer and nails,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["so that it will not totter."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Like scarecrows in a cucumber patch,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["their idols cannot speak."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They must be carried"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because they cannot walk."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Do not fear them, for they can do no harm,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and neither can they do any good.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"There is none like You, O LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You are great, and Your name is mighty in power."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Who would not fear You, O King of nations?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["This is Your due."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For among all the wise men of the nations,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and in all their kingdoms,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["there is none like You."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"But they are altogether senseless and foolish,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["instructed by worthless idols made of wood!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Hammered silver is brought from Tarshish,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and gold from Uphaz—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["the work of a craftsman"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from the hands of a goldsmith."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Their clothes are blue and purple,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["all fashioned by skilled workers."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"But the LORD is the true God;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He is the living God and eternal King."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The earth quakes at His wrath,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the nations cannot endure His indignation."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Thus you are to tell them: “These gods, who have made neither the heavens nor the earth, will perish from this earth and from under these heavens.”",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["10:11"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["The original text of this verse is in Aramaic."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"The LORD made the earth by His power;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He established the world by His wisdom"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and stretched out the heavens by His understanding."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"When He thunders,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the waters in the heavens roar;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["He causes the clouds to rise"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from the ends of the earth."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["He generates the lightning with the rain"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and brings forth the wind from His storehouses."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Every man is senseless and devoid of knowledge;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["every goldsmith is put to shame by his idols."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For his molten images are a fraud,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and there is no breath in them."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"They are worthless, a work to be mocked."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["In the time of their punishment they will perish."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"The Portion of Jacob is not like these,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for He is the Maker of all things,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and Israel is the tribe of His inheritance—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the LORD of Hosts is His name."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Coming Captivity of Judah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Gather up your belongings from this land, you who live under siege.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"For this is what the LORD says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Behold, at this time I will sling out"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the inhabitants of the land"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and bring distress upon them"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["so that they may be captured.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Woe to me because of my brokenness;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["my wound is grievous!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["But I said, “This is truly my sickness,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and I must bear it.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"My tent is destroyed,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and all its ropes are snapped."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["My sons have departed from me"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and are no more."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I have no one left to pitch my tent"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["or set up my curtains."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"For the shepherds have become senseless;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they do not seek the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Therefore they have not prospered,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and all their flock is scattered."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Listen! The sound of a report is coming—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a great commotion from the land to the north."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["It will make the cities of Judah a desolation,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a haunt for jackals.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["10:22"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["serpents"]}," or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["dragons"]},""]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"I know, O LORD, that a man’s way is not his own;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["no one who walks directs his own steps."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Correct me, O LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but only with justice—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["not in Your anger,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["or You will bring me to nothing."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"Pour out Your wrath on the nations"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that do not acknowledge You,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and on the families"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that do not call on Your name."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For they have devoured Jacob;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they have consumed him and finished him off;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they have devastated his homeland."]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"11"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Broken Covenant"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"This is the word that came to Jeremiah from the LORD:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"“Listen to the words of this covenant and tell them to the men of Judah and the residents of Jerusalem.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"You must tell them that this is what the LORD, the God of Israel, says: Cursed is the man who does not obey the words of this covenant,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"which I commanded your forefathers when I brought them out of the land of Egypt, out of the iron furnace, saying, ‘Obey Me, and do everything I command you, and you will be My people, and I will be your God.’",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"This was in order to establish the oath I swore to your forefathers, to give them a land flowing with milk and honey, as it is to this day.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Amen, LORD,” I answered."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Then the LORD said to me, “Proclaim all these words in the cities of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem, saying: Hear the words of this covenant and carry them out.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"For from the time I brought your fathers out of the land of Egypt until today, I strongly warned them again and again,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:7"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["I earnestly warned them, rising up early and warning (them),"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"saying, ‘Obey My voice.’",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Yet they would not obey or incline their ears, but each one followed the stubbornness of his evil heart. So I brought on them all the curses of this covenant I had commanded them to follow but they did not keep.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"And the LORD told me, “There is a conspiracy among the men of Judah and the residents of Jerusalem.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"They have returned to the sins of their forefathers who refused to obey My words. They have followed other gods to serve them. The house of Israel and the house of Judah have broken the covenant I made with their fathers."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Therefore this is what the LORD says: ‘I am about to bring upon them a disaster that they cannot escape. They will cry out to Me, but I will not listen to them.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Then the cities of Judah and the residents of Jerusalem will go and cry out to the gods to which they have been burning incense, but these gods certainly will not save them in their time of disaster.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Your gods are indeed as numerous as your cities, O Judah; the altars of shame you have set up—the altars to burn incense to Baal—are as many as the streets of Jerusalem.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"As for you, do not pray for these people. Do not raise up a cry or a prayer on their behalf, for I will not be listening when they call out to Me in their time of disaster."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"What right has My beloved in My house,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["having carried out so many evil schemes?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Can consecrated meat avert your doom? When you are wicked,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["then you rejoice."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"The LORD once called you a flourishing olive tree,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["beautiful with well-formed fruit."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["But with a mighty roar He will set it on fire,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and its branches will be consumed."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"The LORD of Hosts, who planted you, has decreed disaster against you on account of the evil that the house of Israel and the house of Judah have brought upon themselves, provoking Me to anger by burning incense to Baal.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["A Plot against Jeremiah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Jeremiah 18:18–23)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"And the LORD informed me, so I knew."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Then You showed me their deeds."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"For I was like a gentle lamb led to slaughter;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I did not know that they had plotted against me:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Let us destroy the tree with its fruit;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["let us cut him off from the land of the living,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that his name may be remembered no more.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"O LORD of Hosts, who judges righteously,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["who examines the heart",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:20"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["the kidneys"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"and mind,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["let me see Your vengeance upon them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for to You I have committed my cause."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Therefore this is what the LORD says concerning the people of Anathoth who are seeking your life and saying, “You must not prophesy in the name of the LORD, or you will die by our hand.”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"So this is what the LORD of Hosts says: “I will punish them. Their young men will die by the sword, their sons and daughters by famine.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"There will be no remnant, for I will bring disaster on the people of Anathoth in the year of their punishment.”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"12"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Prosperity of the Wicked"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Righteous are You, O LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["when I plead before You."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Yet about Your judgments"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I wish to contend with You:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Why does the way of the wicked prosper?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Why do all the faithless live at ease?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"You planted them, and they have taken root."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They have grown and produced fruit."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["You are ever on their lips,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but far from their hearts.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:2"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["their kidneys"]},""]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"But You know me, O LORD;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You see me and test my heart toward You."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Drag away the wicked like sheep to the slaughter"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and set them apart for the day of carnage."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"How long will the land mourn"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the grass of every field be withered?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Because of the evil of its residents,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the animals and birds have been swept away,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for the people have said,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“He cannot see what our end will be.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["God’s Answer to Jeremiah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"“If you have raced with men on foot"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they have worn you out,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["how can you compete with horses?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["If you stumble in a peaceful land,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["how will you do in the thickets of the Jordan?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Even your brothers—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["your own father’s household—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["even they have betrayed you;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["even they have cried aloud against you."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Do not trust them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["though they speak well of you."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"I have forsaken My house;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I have abandoned My inheritance."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I have given the beloved of My soul"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["into the hands of her enemies."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"My inheritance has become to Me"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like a lion in the forest."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["She has roared against Me;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["therefore I hate her."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Is not My inheritance to Me"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like a speckled bird of prey"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with other birds of prey",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:9"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["like a speckled hyena with birds of prey"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"circling against her?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Go, gather all the beasts of the field;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["bring them to devour her."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Many shepherds have destroyed My vineyard;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they have trampled My plot of ground."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They have turned My pleasant field"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["into a desolate wasteland."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"They have made it a desolation;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["desolate before Me, it mourns."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["All the land is laid waste,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but no man takes it to heart."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Over all the barren heights in the wilderness"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the destroyers have come,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for the sword of the LORD devours"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from one end of the earth to the other."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["No flesh has peace."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"They have sown wheat but harvested thorns."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They have exhausted themselves to no avail."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Bear the shame of your harvest"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because of the fierce anger of the LORD.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["A Message for Israel’s Neighbors"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Amos 1:1–15)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"This is what the LORD says: “As for all My evil neighbors who attack the inheritance that I bequeathed to My people Israel, I am about to uproot them from their land, and I will uproot the house of Judah from among them.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"But after I have uprooted them, I will once again have compassion on them and return each one to his inheritance and to his land."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"And if they will diligently learn the ways of My people and swear by My name, saying, ‘As surely as the LORD lives’—just as they once taught My people to swear by Baal—then they will be established among My people.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"But if they will not obey, then I will uproot that nation; I will uproot it and destroy it, declares the LORD.”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"13"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Linen Loincloth"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"This is what the LORD said to me: “Go and buy yourself a linen loincloth and put it around your waist, but do not let it touch water.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"So I bought a loincloth in accordance with the word of the LORD, and I put it around my waist."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Then the word of the LORD came to me a second time:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"“Take the loincloth that you bought and are wearing, and go at once to Perath",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["13:4"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or possibly ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["to the Euphrates"]},"; similarly in verses 5–7"]}],"caller":"+"},"and hide it there in a crevice of the rocks.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"So I went and hid it at Perath, as the LORD had commanded me."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Many days later the LORD said to me, “Arise, go to Perath, and get the loincloth that I commanded you to hide there.”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"So I went to Perath and dug up the loincloth, and I took it from the place where I had hidden it. But now it was ruined—of no use at all."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Then the word of the LORD came to me:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"“This is what the LORD says: In the same way I will ruin the pride of Judah and the great pride of Jerusalem.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"These evil people, who refuse to listen to My words, who follow the stubbornness of their own hearts, and who go after other gods to serve and worship them, they will be like this loincloth—of no use at all."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"For just as a loincloth clings to a man’s waist, so I have made the whole house of Israel and the whole house of Judah cling to Me, declares the LORD, so that they might be My people for My renown and praise and glory. But they did not listen."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Wineskins"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Therefore you are to tell them that this is what the LORD, the God of Israel, says: ‘Every wineskin shall be filled with wine.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["And when they reply, ‘Don’t we surely know that every wineskin should be filled with wine?’",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"then you are to tell them that this is what the LORD says: ‘I am going to fill with drunkenness all who live in this land—the kings who sit on David’s throne, the priests, the prophets, and all the people of Jerusalem.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"I will smash them against one another, fathers and sons alike, declares the LORD. I will allow no mercy or pity or compassion to keep Me from destroying them.’”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Captivity Threatened"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Listen and give heed. Do not be arrogant,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the LORD has spoken."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Give glory to the LORD your God"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["before He brings darkness,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["before your feet stumble"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["on the dusky mountains."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["You wait for light,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but He turns it into deep gloom and thick darkness."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"But if you do not listen,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will weep in secret because of your pride."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["My eyes will overflow with tears,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because the LORD’s flock has been taken captive."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Say to the king"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and to the queen mother:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Take a lowly seat,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for your glorious crowns have fallen from your heads.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"The cities of the Negev have been shut tight,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and no one can open them."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["All Judah has been carried into exile,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["wholly taken captive."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Lift up your eyes and see"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["those coming from the north."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Where is the flock entrusted to you,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the sheep that were your pride?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"What will you say when He sets over you"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["close allies whom you yourself trained?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Will not pangs of anguish grip you,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["as they do a woman in labor?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"And if you ask yourself,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“Why has this happened to me?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["It is because of the magnitude of your iniquity"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that your skirts have been stripped off"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and your body has been exposed.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["13:22"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["and your heels have suffered violence"]},""]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Can the Ethiopian",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["13:23"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["that Cushite"]},"; that is, probably a person from the upper Nile region"]}],"caller":"+"},"change his skin,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["or the leopard his spots?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Neither are you able to do good—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["you who are accustomed to doing evil."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"“I will scatter you like chaff"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["driven by the desert wind."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"This is your lot,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the portion I have measured to you,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“because you have forgotten Me"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and trusted in falsehood."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"So I will pull your skirts up over your face,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that your shame may be seen."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"Your adulteries and lustful neighings,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["your shameless prostitution"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["on the hills and in the fields—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I have seen your detestable acts."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Woe to you, O Jerusalem!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["How long will you remain unclean?”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"14"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Drought, Famine, Sword, and Plague"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"This is the word of the LORD that came to Jeremiah concerning the drought:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"“Judah mourns"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and her gates languish."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Her people wail for the land,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and a cry goes up from Jerusalem."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"The nobles send their servants for water;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they go to the cisterns, but find no water;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["their jars return empty."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They are ashamed and humiliated;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they cover their heads."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"The ground is cracked"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because no rain has fallen on the land."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The farmers are ashamed;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they cover their heads."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Even the doe in the field deserts her newborn fawn"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because there is no grass."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Wild donkeys stand on barren heights;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they pant for air like jackals;",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["14:6"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["serpents"]}," or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["dragons"]},""]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["their eyes fail for lack of pasture.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Although our iniquities testify against us, O LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["act for the sake of Your name."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Indeed, our rebellions are many;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["we have sinned against You."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"O Hope of Israel,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["its Savior in times of distress,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["why are You like a stranger in the land,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like a traveler who stays but a night?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Why are You like a man taken by surprise,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like a warrior powerless to save?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Yet You are among us, O LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and we are called by Your name."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Do not forsake us!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"This is what the LORD says about this people:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Truly they love to wander;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they have not restrained their feet."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["So the LORD does not accept them;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He will now remember their iniquity"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and punish them for their sins.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Then the LORD said to me, “Do not pray for the well-being of this people.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Although they may fast, I will not listen to their cry; although they may offer burnt offerings and grain offerings, I will not accept them. Instead, I will finish them off by sword and famine and plague.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"“Ah, Lord GOD!” I replied, “Look, the prophets are telling them, ‘You will not see the sword or suffer famine, but I will give you lasting peace in this place.’”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"“The prophets are prophesying lies in My name,” replied the LORD. “I did not send them or appoint them or speak to them. They are prophesying to you a false vision, a worthless divination, the futility and delusion of their own minds."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Therefore this is what the LORD says about the prophets who prophesy in My name: I did not send them, yet they say, ‘No sword or famine will touch this land.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["By sword and famine these very prophets will meet their end!",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"And the people to whom they prophesy will be thrown into the streets of Jerusalem because of famine and sword. There will be no one to bury them or their wives, their sons or their daughters. I will pour out their own evil upon them."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"You are to speak this word to them:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘My eyes overflow with tears;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["day and night they do not cease,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for the virgin daughter of my people"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["has been shattered by a crushing blow,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a severely grievous wound."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"If I go out to the country,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I see those slain by the sword;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["if I enter the city,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I see those ravaged by famine!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For both prophet and priest"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["travel to a land they do not know.’”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["A Prayer for Mercy"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Isaiah 63:15–19)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Have You rejected Judah completely?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Do You despise Zion?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Why have You stricken us"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["so that we are beyond healing?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["We hoped for peace,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but no good has come,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and for the time of healing,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but there was only terror."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"We acknowledge our wickedness, O LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the guilt of our fathers;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["indeed, we have sinned against You."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"For the sake of Your name do not despise us;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["do not disgrace Your glorious throne."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Remember Your covenant with us;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["do not break it."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Can the worthless idols of the nations bring rain?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Do the skies alone send showers?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Is this not by You, O LORD our God?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["So we put our hope in You,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for You have done all these things."]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"15"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Judgment to Continue"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Then the LORD said to me: “Even if Moses and Samuel should stand before Me, My heart would not go out to this people. Send them from My presence, and let them go!",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"If they ask you, ‘Where shall we go?’ you are to tell them that this is what the LORD says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘Those destined for death, to death;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["those destined for the sword, to the sword;",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["15:2"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["See",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Revelation 13:10"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["those destined for famine, to famine;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and those destined for captivity, to captivity.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"I will appoint over them four kinds of destroyers, declares the LORD: the sword to kill, the dogs to drag away, and the birds of the air and beasts of the earth to devour and destroy.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"I will make them a horror to all the kingdoms of the earth because of what Manasseh son of Hezekiah king of Judah did in Jerusalem."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Who will have pity on you, O Jerusalem?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Who will mourn for you?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Who will turn aside"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to ask about your welfare?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"You have forsaken Me, declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You have turned your back."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["So I will stretch out My hand against you"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and I will destroy you;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I am weary of showing compassion."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"I will scatter them with a winnowing fork"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["at the gates of the land."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will bereave and destroy My people"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["who have not turned from their ways."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"I will make their widows more numerous"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["than the sand of the sea."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will bring a destroyer at noon"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["against the mothers of young men."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will suddenly bring upon them"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["anguish and dismay."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"The mother of seven will grow faint;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["she will breathe her last breath."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Her sun will set while it is still day;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["she will be disgraced and humiliated."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["And the rest I will put to the sword"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in the presence of their enemies,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jeremiah’s Woe"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Woe to me, my mother,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that you have borne me,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["a man of strife and conflict"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in all the land."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I have neither lent nor borrowed,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["yet everyone curses me."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"The LORD said:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Surely I will deliver you for a good purpose;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["surely I will intercede with your enemy"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["in your time of trouble,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in your time of distress."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Can anyone smash iron—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["iron from the north—or bronze?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Your wealth and your treasures"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will give up as plunder,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["without charge for all your sins"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["within all your borders."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Then I will enslave you to your enemies"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in a land",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["15:14"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Some Hebrew manuscripts, LXX, and Syriac (see also",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Jeremiah 17:4"]},"); most Hebrew manuscripts ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Then I will cause your enemies to bring you into a land"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"you do not know,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for My anger will kindle a fire"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that will burn against you.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"You understand, O LORD;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["remember me and attend to me."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Avenge me against my persecutors."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["In Your patience, do not take me away."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Know that I endure reproach for Your honor."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Your words were found, and I ate them."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Your words became my joy"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and my heart’s delight."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For I bear Your name,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["O LORD God of Hosts."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"I never sat with the band of revelers,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["nor did I celebrate with them."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Because Your hand was on me, I sat alone,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for You have filled me with indignation."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Why is my pain unending,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and my wound incurable,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["refusing to be healed?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["You have indeed become like a mirage to me—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["water that is not there."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The LORD’s Promise"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Therefore this is what the LORD says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“If you return, I will restore you;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["you will stand in My presence."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["And if you speak words that are noble instead of worthless,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["you will be My spokesman."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["It is they who must turn to you,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but you must not turn to them."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Then I will make you a wall to this people,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a fortified wall of bronze;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["they will fight against you"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but will not overcome you,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for I am with you to save and deliver you,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"I will deliver you from the hand of the wicked"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and redeem you from the grasp of the ruthless.”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"16"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Disaster Predicted"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Then the word of the LORD came to me, saying,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"“You must not marry or have sons or daughters in this place.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"For this is what the LORD says concerning the sons and daughters born in this place, and the mothers who bore them, and the fathers who fathered them in this land:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"“They will die from deadly diseases. They will not be mourned or buried, but will lie like dung on the ground. They will be finished off by sword and famine, and their corpses will become food for the birds of the air and beasts of the earth.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Indeed, this is what the LORD says: “Do not enter a house where there is a funeral meal. Do not go to mourn or show sympathy, for I have removed from this people My peace, My loving devotion, and My compassion,” declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"“Both great and small will die in this land. They will not be buried or mourned, nor will anyone cut himself or shave his head for them.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"No food will be offered to comfort those who mourn the dead; not even a cup of consolation will be given for the loss of a father or mother."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"You must not enter a house where there is feasting and sit down with them to eat and drink.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"For this is what the LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel, says: I am going to remove from this place, before your very eyes and in your days, the sounds of joy and gladness, the voices of the bride and bridegroom."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"When you tell these people all these things, they will ask you, ‘Why has the LORD pronounced all this great disaster against us? What is our iniquity? What is the sin that we have committed against the LORD our God?’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Then you are to answer them: ‘It is because your fathers have forsaken Me, declares the LORD, and followed other gods, and served and worshiped them. They abandoned Me and did not keep My instruction.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"And you have done more evil than your fathers. See how each of you follows the stubbornness of his evil heart instead of obeying Me.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"So I will cast you out of this land into a land that neither you nor your fathers have known. There you will serve other gods day and night, for I will show you no favor.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["God Will Restore Israel"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Yet behold, the days are coming, declares the LORD, when they will no longer say, ‘As surely as the LORD lives, who brought the Israelites up out of the land of Egypt.’",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Instead they will say, ‘As surely as the LORD lives, who brought the Israelites up out of the land of the north and all the other lands to which He had banished them.’ For I will return them to their land that I gave to their forefathers."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"But for now I will send for many fishermen, declares the LORD, and they will catch them. After that I will send for many hunters, and they will hunt them down on every mountain and hill, even from the clefts of the rocks."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"For My eyes are on all their ways. They are not hidden from My face, and their guilt is not concealed from My eyes.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"And I will first repay them double their iniquity and their sin, because they have defiled My land with the carcasses of their detestable idols, and they have filled My inheritance with their abominations.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"O LORD, my strength and my fortress,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["my refuge in the day of distress,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["the nations will come to You"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from the ends of the earth, and they will say,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Our fathers inherited nothing but lies,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["worthless idols of no benefit at all."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Can man make gods for himself?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Such are not gods!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"“Therefore behold, I will inform them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and this time I will make them know"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["My power and My might;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["then they will know"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that My name is the LORD..’’]"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"17"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Sin and Punishment of Judah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"“The sin of Judah is written with an iron stylus,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["engraved with a diamond point"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["on the tablets of their hearts"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and on the horns of their altars."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"Even their children remember their altars and Asherah poles"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["by the green trees and on the high hills."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"O My mountain in the countryside,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will give over your wealth"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and all your treasures as plunder,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["because of the sin of your high places,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["within all your borders."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"And you yourself will relinquish"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the inheritance that I gave you."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will enslave you to your enemies"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in a land that you do not know,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for you have kindled My anger;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["it will burn forever.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"This is what the LORD says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Cursed is the man who trusts in mankind,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["who makes mere flesh his strength",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["17:5"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["arm"]},""]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and turns his heart from the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"He will be like a shrub in the desert;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["he will not see when prosperity comes."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["He will dwell in the parched places of the desert,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in a salt land where no one lives."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"But blessed is the man who trusts in the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["whose confidence is in Him."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"He is like a tree planted by the waters"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that sends out its roots toward the stream."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["It does not fear when the heat comes,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and its leaves are always green."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["It does not worry in a year of drought,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["nor does it cease to produce fruit."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"The heart is deceitful above all things"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and beyond cure."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Who can understand it?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"I, the LORD, search the heart;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I examine the mind",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["17:10"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["kidneys"]},""]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["to reward a man according to his way,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["by what his deeds deserve."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Like a partridge hatching eggs it did not lay"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["is the man who makes a fortune unjustly."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["In the middle of his days his riches will desert him,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and in the end he will be the fool.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jeremiah’s Prayer for Deliverance"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"A glorious throne, exalted from the beginning,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["is the place of our sanctuary."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"O LORD, the hope of Israel,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["all who abandon You will be put to shame."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["All who turn away will be written in the dust,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for they have abandoned the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the fountain of living water."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Heal me, O LORD, and I will be healed;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["save me, and I will be saved,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for You are my praise."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Behold, they keep saying to me,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“Where is the word of the LORD?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Let it come now!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"But I have not run away from being Your shepherd;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I have not desired the day of despair."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["You know that the utterance of my lips"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["was spoken in Your presence."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Do not become a terror to me;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You are my refuge in the day of disaster."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Let my persecutors be put to shame,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but do not let me be put to shame."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Let them be terrified,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but do not let me be terrified."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Bring upon them the day of disaster"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and shatter them with double destruction."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Restoring the Sabbath"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Nehemiah 13:15–22)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"This is what the LORD said to me: “Go and stand at the gate of the people, through which the kings of Judah go in and out; and stand at all the other gates of Jerusalem."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Say to them, ‘Hear the word of the LORD, O kings of Judah, all people of Judah and Jerusalem who enter through these gates.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"This is what the LORD says: Take heed for yourselves; do not carry a load or bring it through the gates of Jerusalem on the Sabbath day.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"You must not carry a load out of your houses or do any work on the Sabbath day, but you must keep the Sabbath day holy, just as I commanded your forefathers.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Yet they would not listen or incline their ear, but they stiffened their necks and would not listen or receive My discipline."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"If, however, you listen carefully to Me, says the LORD, and bring no load through the gates of this city on the Sabbath day, and keep the Sabbath day holy, and do no work on it,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"then kings and princes will enter through the gates of this city. They will sit on the throne of David, riding in chariots and on horses with their officials, along with the men of Judah and the residents of Jerusalem, and this city will be inhabited forever.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"And people will come from the cities of Judah and the places around Jerusalem, from the land of Benjamin, and from the foothills,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["17:26"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Shephelah"]}," or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["lowlands"]},"; that is, the western foothills of Judea"]}],"caller":"+"},"the hill country, and the Negev, bringing burnt offerings and sacrifices, grain offerings and frankincense, and thank offerings to the house of the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"But if you do not listen to Me to keep the Sabbath day holy by not carrying a load while entering the gates of Jerusalem on the Sabbath day, then I will kindle an unquenchable fire in its gates to consume the citadels of Jerusalem.’”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"18"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Potter and the Clay"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"This is the word that came to Jeremiah from the LORD:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"“Go down at once to the potter’s house, and there I will give you My message.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"So I went down to the potter’s house and saw him working at the wheel.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"But the vessel that he was shaping from the clay became flawed in his hand; so he formed it into another vessel, as it seemed best for him to do."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Then the word of the LORD came to me, saying,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"“O house of Israel, declares the LORD, can I not treat you as this potter treats his clay? Just like clay in the potter’s hand, so are you in My hand, O house of Israel."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"At any time I might announce that a nation or kingdom will be uprooted, torn down, and destroyed.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"But if that nation I warned turns from its evil, then I will relent of the disaster I had planned to bring."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"And if at another time I announce that I will build up and establish a nation or kingdom,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"and if it does evil in My sight and does not listen to My voice, then I will relent of the good I had intended for it."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Now therefore, tell the men of Judah and the residents of Jerusalem that this is what the LORD says: ‘Behold, I am planning a disaster for you and devising a plan against you. Turn now, each of you, from your evil ways, and correct your ways and deeds.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"But they will reply, ‘It is hopeless. We will follow our own plans, and each of us will act according to the stubbornness of his evil heart.’”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Therefore this is what the LORD says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Inquire among the nations:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Who has ever heard things like these?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Virgin Israel has done a most terrible thing."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Does the snow of Lebanon"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["ever leave its rocky slopes?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Or do its cool waters flowing from a distance"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["ever run dry?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Yet My people have forgotten Me."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They burn incense to worthless idols"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that make them stumble in their ways,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["leaving the ancient roads"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to walk on rutted bypaths"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["instead of on the highway."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"They have made their land a desolation,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a perpetual object of scorn;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["all who pass by will be appalled"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and shake their heads."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"I will scatter them before the enemy"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like the east wind."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will show them My back and not My face"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in the day of their calamity.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Another Plot against Jeremiah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Jeremiah 11:18–23)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Then some said, “Come, let us make plans against Jeremiah, for the law will never be lost to the priest, nor counsel to the wise, nor an oracle to the prophet. Come, let us denounce him and pay no heed to any of his words.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Attend to me, O LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Hear what my accusers are saying!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Should good be repaid with evil?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Yet they have dug a pit for me."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Remember how I stood before You"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to speak good on their behalf,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to turn Your wrath from them."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Therefore, hand their children over to famine;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["pour out the power of the sword upon them."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Let their wives become childless and widowed;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["let their husbands be slain by disease,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["their young men struck down by the sword in battle."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Let a cry be heard from their houses"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["when You suddenly bring raiders against them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for they have dug a pit to capture me"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and have hidden snares for my feet."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"But You, O LORD, know all their deadly plots against me."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Do not wipe out their guilt"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["or blot out their sin from Your sight."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Let them be overthrown before You;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["deal with them in the time of Your anger."]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"19"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Broken Jar"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"This is what the LORD says: “Go and buy a clay jar from a potter. Take some of the elders of the people and leaders of the priests,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"and go out to the Valley of Ben-hinnom near the entrance of the Potsherd Gate."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Proclaim there the words I speak to you,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"saying, ‘Hear the word of the LORD, O kings of Judah and residents of Jerusalem. This is what the LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel, says: I am going to bring such disaster on this place that the ears of all who hear of it will ring,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"because they have abandoned Me and made this a foreign place. They have burned incense in this place to other gods that neither they nor their fathers nor the kings of Judah have ever known. They have filled this place with the blood of the innocent.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"They have built high places to Baal on which to burn their children in the fire as offerings to Baal—something I never commanded or mentioned, nor did it even enter My mind."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"So behold, the days are coming, declares the LORD, when this place will no longer be called Topheth or the Valley of Ben-hinnom, but the Valley of Slaughter.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"And in this place I will ruin",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["19:7"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["The Hebrew term for ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["ruin"]}," sounds like the Hebrew for ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["jar"]},"; see verses 1 and 10."]}],"caller":"+"},"the plans of Judah and Jerusalem. I will make them fall by the sword before their enemies, by the hands of those who seek their lives, and I will give their carcasses as food to the birds of the air and the beasts of the earth."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"I will make this city a desolation and an object of scorn.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["19:8"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["and a hissing"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"All who pass by will be appalled and will scoff at all her wounds.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"I will make them eat the flesh of their sons and daughters, and they will eat one another’s flesh in the siege and distress inflicted on them by their enemies who seek their lives.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Then you are to shatter the jar in the presence of the men who accompany you,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"and you are to proclaim to them that this is what the LORD of Hosts says: I will shatter this nation and this city, like one shatters a potter’s jar that can never again be repaired. They will bury the dead in Topheth until there is no more room to bury them."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"This is what I will do to this place and to its residents, declares the LORD. I will make this city like Topheth.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"The houses of Jerusalem and the houses of the kings of Judah will be defiled like that place, Topheth—all the houses on whose rooftops they burned incense to all the host of heaven and poured out drink offerings to other gods.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Then Jeremiah returned from Topheth, where the LORD had sent him to prophesy, and he stood in the courtyard of the house of the LORD and proclaimed to all the people,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"“This is what the LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel, says: ‘Behold, I am about to bring on this city and on all the villages around it every disaster I have pronounced against them, because they have stiffened their necks so as not to heed My words.’”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"20"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Pashhur Persecutes Jeremiah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"When Pashhur the priest, the son of Immer and the chief official in the house of the LORD, heard Jeremiah prophesying these things,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"he had Jeremiah the prophet beaten and put in the stocks at the Upper Gate of Benjamin, which was by the house of the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"The next day, when Pashhur released Jeremiah from the stocks, Jeremiah said to him, “The LORD does not call you Pashhur, but Magor-missabib.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:3"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Magor-missabib"]}," means ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["terror on every side"]}," or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["the man who lives in terror"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"For this is what the LORD says: ‘I will make you a terror to yourself and to all your friends. They will fall by the sword of their enemies before your very eyes. And I will hand Judah over to the king of Babylon, and he will carry them away to Babylon and put them to the sword.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"I will give away all the wealth of this city—all its products and valuables, and all the treasures of the kings of Judah—to their enemies. They will plunder them, seize them, and carry them off to Babylon.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"And you, Pashhur, and all who live in your house, will go into captivity. You will go to Babylon, and there you will die and be buried—you and all your friends to whom you have prophesied these lies.’”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jeremiah’s Complaint"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"You have deceived me, O LORD, and I was deceived."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You have overcome me and prevailed."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I am a laughingstock all day long;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["everyone mocks me."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"For whenever I speak, I cry out;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I proclaim violence and destruction."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For the word of the LORD has become to me"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a reproach and derision all day long."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"If I say, “I will not mention Him"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["or speak any more in His name,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["His message becomes a fire burning in my heart,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["shut up in my bones,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and I become weary of holding it in,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and I cannot prevail."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"For I have heard the whispering of many:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“Terror is on every side!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Report him; let us report him!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["All my trusted friends"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["watch for my fall:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Perhaps he will be deceived"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["so that we may prevail against him"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and take our vengeance upon him.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"But the LORD is with me like a fearsome warrior."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Therefore, my persecutors will stumble and will not prevail."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Since they have not succeeded, they will be utterly put to shame,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with an everlasting disgrace that will never be forgotten."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"O LORD of Hosts, who examines the righteous,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["who sees the heart",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:12"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["kidneys"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"and mind,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["let me see Your vengeance upon them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for to You I have committed my cause."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Sing to the LORD!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Praise the LORD!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For He rescues the life of the needy"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from the hands of evildoers."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Cursed be the day I was born!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["May the day my mother bore me never be blessed."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Cursed be the man who brought my father the news,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["saying, “A son is born to you,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["bringing him great joy."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"May that man be like the cities"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that the LORD overthrew without compassion."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["May he hear an outcry in the morning"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and a battle cry at noon,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"because he did not kill me in the womb"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["so that my mother might have been my grave,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and her womb forever enlarged."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Why did I come out of the womb"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to see only trouble and sorrow,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and to end my days in shame?"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"21"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jerusalem Will Fall to Babylon"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"This is the word that came to Jeremiah from the LORD when King Zedekiah sent to him Pashhur son of Malchijah and the priest Zephaniah son of Maaseiah. They said,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"“Please inquire of the LORD on our behalf, since Nebuchadnezzar",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["21:2"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Nebuchadrezzar"]},", a variant of ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Nebuchadnezzar"]}," (king of Babylon), which occurs frequently in Jeremiah. The latter spelling is used throughout Jeremiah for consistency."]}],"caller":"+"},"king of Babylon is waging war against us. Perhaps the LORD will perform for us something like all His past wonders, so that Nebuchadnezzar will withdraw from us.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"But Jeremiah answered, “You are to tell Zedekiah that",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"this is what the LORD, the God of Israel, says: ‘I will turn against you the weapons of war in your hands, with which you are fighting the king of Babylon and the Chaldeans",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["21:4"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, the Babylonians; also in verse 9"]}],"caller":"+"},"who besiege you outside the wall, and I will assemble their forces in the center of this city.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"And I Myself will fight against you with an outstretched hand and a mighty arm, with anger, fury, and great wrath.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"I will strike down the residents of this city, both man and beast. They will die in a terrible plague.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"‘After that,’ declares the LORD, ‘I will hand over Zedekiah king of Judah, his officers, and the people in this city who survive the plague and sword and famine, to Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon and to their enemies who seek their lives. He will put them to the sword; he will not spare them or show pity or compassion.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Furthermore, you are to tell this people that this is what the LORD says: ‘Behold, I set before you the way of life and the way of death.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Whoever stays in this city will die by sword and famine and plague, but whoever goes out and surrenders to the Chaldeans who besiege you will live; he will retain his life like a spoil of war.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"For I have set My face against this city to bring disaster and not good, declares the LORD. It will be delivered into the hand of the king of Babylon, who will destroy it with fire.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["A Message to the House of David"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Moreover, tell the house of the king of Judah to hear the word of the LORD.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"O house of David, this is what the LORD says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘Administer justice every morning,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and rescue the victim of robbery"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["from the hand of his oppressor,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["or My wrath will go forth like fire"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and burn with no one to extinguish it"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because of their evil deeds."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Behold, I am against you who dwell above the valley,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["atop the rocky plateau—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["declares the LORD—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["you who say, “Who can come against us?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Who can enter our dwellings?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"I will punish you as your deeds deserve,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will kindle a fire in your forest"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that will consume everything around you.’”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"22"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["A Warning to Judah’s Kings"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"This is what the LORD says: “Go down to the palace of the king of Judah and proclaim this message there,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"saying, ‘Hear the word of the LORD, O king of Judah, who sits on the throne of David—you and your officials and your people who enter these gates.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"This is what the LORD says: Administer justice and righteousness. Rescue the victim of robbery from the hand of his oppressor. Do no wrong or violence to the foreigner, the fatherless, or the widow. Do not shed innocent blood in this place."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"For if you will indeed carry out these commands, then kings who sit on David’s throne will enter through the gates of this palace riding on chariots and horses—they and their officials and their people.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"But if you do not obey these words, then I swear by Myself, declares the LORD, that this house will become a pile of rubble.’”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["A Warning about the Palace"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"For this is what the LORD says concerning the house of the king of Judah:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“You are like Gilead to Me,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like the summit of Lebanon;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["but I will surely turn you into a desert,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like cities that are uninhabited."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"I will appoint destroyers against you,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["each man with his weapons,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and they will cut down the choicest of your cedars"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and throw them into the fire."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"And many nations will pass by this city and ask one another, ‘Why has the LORD done such a thing to this great city?’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Then people will reply, ‘Because they have forsaken the covenant of the LORD their God and have worshiped and served other gods.’”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["A Warning about Shallum"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Do not weep for him who is dead;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["do not mourn his loss."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Weep bitterly for him who is exiled,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for he will never return"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to see his native land."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"For this is what the LORD says concerning Shallum",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["22:11"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Shallum"]}," was also called ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Jehoahaz"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"son of Josiah, king of Judah, who succeeded his father Josiah but has gone forth from this place: “He will never return,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"but he will die in the place to which he was exiled; he will never see this land again.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["A Warning about Jehoiakim"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"“Woe to him who builds his palace by unrighteousness,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and his upper rooms without justice,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["who makes his countrymen serve without pay,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and fails to pay their wages,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"who says, ‘I will build myself a great palace,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with spacious upper rooms.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["So he cuts windows in it,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["panels it with cedar,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and paints it with vermilion."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Does it make you a king to excel",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["22:15"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["because you enclose yourself"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"in cedar?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Did not your father have food and drink?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["He administered justice and righteousness,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and so it went well with him."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"He took up the cause of the poor and needy,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and so it went well with him."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Is this not what it means to know Me?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"“But your eyes and heart are set on nothing"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["except your own dishonest gain,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["on shedding innocent blood,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["on practicing extortion and oppression.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Therefore this is what the LORD says concerning Jehoiakim son of Josiah king of Judah:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“They will not mourn for him:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘Alas, my brother! Alas, my sister!’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They will not mourn for him:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘Alas, my master! Alas, his splendor!’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"He will be buried like a donkey,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["dragged away and thrown outside the gates of Jerusalem."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Go up to Lebanon and cry out;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["raise your voice in Bashan;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["cry out from Abarim,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for all your lovers have been crushed."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"I warned you when you were secure."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You said, ‘I will not listen.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["This has been your way from youth,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that you have not obeyed My voice."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"The wind will drive away all your shepherds,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and your lovers will go into captivity."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Then you will be ashamed and humiliated"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because of all your wickedness."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"O inhabitant of Lebanon,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["22:23"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, the palace in Jerusalem; see",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["1 Kings 7:2"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["nestled in the cedars,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["how you will groan when pangs of anguish come upon you,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["agony like a woman in labor.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["A Warning to Coniah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"“As surely as I live,” declares the LORD, “even if you, Coniah",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["22:24"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Coniah"]}," is a variant of ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Jehoiachin"]},"; also in verse 28."]}],"caller":"+"},"son of Jehoiakim king of Judah, were a signet ring on My right hand, I would pull you off.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"In fact, I will hand you over to those you dread, who want to take your life—to Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon and to the Chaldeans.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["22:25"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, the Babylonians"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"I will hurl you and the mother who gave you birth into another land, where neither of you were born—and there you both will die.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"You will never return to the land for which you long.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"Is this man Coniah a despised and shattered pot,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a jar that no one wants?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Why are he and his descendants hurled out"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and cast into a land they do not know?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"O land, land, land,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["hear the word of the LORD!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"This is what the LORD says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Enroll this man as childless,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a man who will not prosper in his lifetime."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["None of his descendants will prosper"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to sit on the throne of David"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["or to rule again in Judah.”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"23"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["David’s Righteous Branch"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"“Woe to the shepherds who destroy and scatter the sheep of My pasture!” declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"Therefore this is what the LORD, the God of Israel, says about the shepherds who tend My people: “You have scattered My flock and driven them away, and have not attended to them. Behold, I will attend to you for the evil of your deeds, declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Then I Myself will gather the remnant of My flock from all the lands to which I have banished them, and I will return them to their pasture, where they will be fruitful and multiply.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"I will raise up shepherds over them who will tend them, and they will no longer be afraid or dismayed, nor will any go missing, declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Behold, the days are coming,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["declares the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["when I will raise up for David",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:5"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["up for David’s line"]},""]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a righteous Branch,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and He will reign wisely as King"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will administer justice and righteousness in the land."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"In His days Judah will be saved,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and Israel will dwell securely."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["And this is His name by which He will be called:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The LORD Our Righteousness.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:6"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["YHWH Tsidqenu"]},""]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"So behold, the days are coming, declares the LORD, when they will no longer say, ‘As surely as the LORD lives, who brought the Israelites up out of the land of Egypt.’",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Instead they will say, ‘As surely as the LORD lives, who brought and led the descendants of the house of Israel up out of the land of the north and all the other lands to which He had banished them.’ Then they will dwell once more in their own land.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Lying Prophets"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"As for the prophets:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["My heart is broken within me,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and all my bones tremble."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I have become like a drunkard,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like a man overcome by wine,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["because of the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because of His holy words."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"For the land is full of adulterers—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because of the curse, the land mourns"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the pastures of the wilderness have dried up—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["their course is evil"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and their power is misused."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"“For both prophet and priest are ungodly;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["even in My house I have found their wickedness,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"“Therefore their path will become slick;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they will be driven away into the darkness and fall into it."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For I will bring disaster upon them"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in the year of their punishment,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"“Among the prophets of Samaria"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I saw an offensive thing:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They prophesied by Baal"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and led My people Israel astray."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"And among the prophets of Jerusalem"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I have seen a horrible thing:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They commit adultery"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and walk in lies."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They strengthen the hands of evildoers,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["so that no one turns his back on wickedness."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They are all like Sodom to Me;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the people of Jerusalem are like Gomorrah.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Therefore this is what the LORD of Hosts says concerning the prophets:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“I will feed them wormwood"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and give them poisoned water to drink,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for from the prophets of Jerusalem"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["ungodliness has spread throughout the land.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"This is what the LORD of Hosts says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Do not listen to the words of the prophets who prophesy to you."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They are filling you with false hopes."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They speak visions from their own minds,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["not from the mouth of the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"They keep saying to those who despise Me,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘The LORD says that you will have peace,’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and to everyone who walks in the stubbornness of his own heart,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘No harm will come to you.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"But which of them has stood in the council of the LORD"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to see and hear His word?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Who has given heed to His word"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and obeyed it?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Behold, the storm of the LORD"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["has gone out with fury,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["a whirlwind swirling down"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["upon the heads of the wicked."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"The anger of the LORD will not turn back"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["until He has fully accomplished the purposes of His heart."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["In the days to come"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["you will understand this clearly."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"I did not send these prophets,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["yet they have run with their message;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I did not speak to them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["yet they have prophesied."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"But if they had stood in My council,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they would have proclaimed My words to My people"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and turned them back"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from their evil ways and deeds.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"“Am I only a God nearby,” declares the LORD, “and not a God far away?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"“Can a man hide in secret places where I cannot see him?” declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Do I not fill the heavens and the earth?” declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"“I have heard the sayings of the prophets who prophesy lies in My name: ‘I had a dream! I had a dream!’",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"How long will this continue in the hearts of these prophets who prophesy falsehood, these prophets of the delusion of their own minds?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"They suppose the dreams that they tell one another will make My people forget My name, just as their fathers forgot My name through the worship of Baal."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"Let the prophet who has a dream retell it, but let him who has My word speak it truthfully. For what is straw compared to grain?” declares the LORD.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"“Is not My word like fire,” declares the LORD, “and like a hammer that smashes a rock?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"“Therefore behold,” declares the LORD, “I am against the prophets who steal from one another words they attribute to Me.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"“Yes,” declares the LORD, “I am against the prophets who wag their own tongues and proclaim, ‘The LORD declares it.’”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"“Indeed,” declares the LORD, “I am against those who prophesy false dreams and retell them to lead My people astray with their reckless lies. It was not I who sent them or commanded them, and they are of no benefit at all to these people,” declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["False Prophecies"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"“Now when this people or a prophet or priest asks you, ‘What is the burden of the LORD?’ you are to say to them, ‘What burden? I will forsake you, declares the LORD.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"As for the prophet or priest or anyone who claims, ‘This is the burden of the LORD,’ I will punish that man and his household."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"This is what each man is to say to his friend and to his brother: ‘What has the LORD answered?’ or ‘What has the LORD spoken?’",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"But refer no more to the burden of the LORD, for each man’s word becomes the burden, so that you pervert the words of the living God, the LORD of Hosts, our God."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"Thus you are to say to the prophet: ‘What has the LORD answered you?’ and ‘What has the LORD spoken?’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"But if you claim, ‘This is the burden of the LORD,’ then this is what the LORD says: Because you have said, ‘This is the burden of the LORD,’ and I specifically told you not to make this claim,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"therefore I will surely forget you and will cast you out of My presence, both you and the city that I gave to you and your fathers.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40"},"And I will bring upon you everlasting shame and perpetual humiliation that will never be forgotten.”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"24"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Good and Bad Figs"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"After Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon had carried away Jeconiah",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["24:1"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Jeconiah"]}," is a variant of ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Jehoiachin"]},"; see",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["2 Kings 24:12"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"son of Jehoiakim king of Judah, as well as the officials of Judah and the craftsmen and metalsmiths from Jerusalem, and had brought them to Babylon,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["24:1"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["metalsmiths, and had brought them from Jerusalem to Babylon"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"the LORD showed me two baskets of figs placed in front of the temple of the LORD.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"One basket had very good figs, like those that ripen early, but the other basket contained very poor figs, so bad they could not be eaten."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"“Jeremiah,” the LORD asked, “what do you see?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Figs!” I replied. “The good figs are very good, but the bad figs are very bad, so bad they cannot be eaten.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Then the word of the LORD came to me, saying,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"“This is what the LORD, the God of Israel, says: ‘Like these good figs, so I regard as good the exiles from Judah, whom I have sent away from this place to the land of the Chaldeans.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["24:5"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, the Babylonians"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"I will keep My eyes on them for good and will return them to this land. I will build them up and not tear them down; I will plant them and not uproot them.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"I will give them a heart to know Me, that I am the LORD. They will be My people, and I will be their God, for they will return to Me with all their heart."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"But like the bad figs, so bad they cannot be eaten,’ says the LORD, ‘so will I deal with Zedekiah king of Judah, his officials, and the remnant of Jerusalem—those remaining in this land and those living in the land of Egypt.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"I will make them a horror and an offense to all the kingdoms of the earth, a disgrace and an object of scorn, ridicule, and cursing wherever I have banished them.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"And I will send against them sword and famine and plague, until they have perished from the land that I gave to them and their fathers.’”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"25"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Seventy Years of Captivity"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"This is the word that came to Jeremiah concerning all the people of Judah in the fourth year of Jehoiakim son of Josiah king of Judah, which was the first year of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"So the prophet Jeremiah spoke to all the people of Judah and all the residents of Jerusalem as follows:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"“From the thirteenth year of Josiah son of Amon king of Judah until this very day—twenty-three years—the word of the LORD has come to me, and I have spoken to you again and again,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["25:3"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["I have spoken to you, rising up early and speaking,"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"but you have not listened.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"And the LORD has sent all His servants the prophets to you again and again,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["25:4"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["to you, rising up early and sending (them),"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"but you have not listened or inclined your ear to hear."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"The prophets told you, ‘Turn now, each of you, from your evil ways and deeds, and you can dwell in the land that the LORD has given to you and your fathers forever and ever.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Do not follow other gods to serve and worship them, and do not provoke Me to anger with the works of your hands. Then I will do you no harm.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"‘But to your own harm, you have not listened to Me,’ declares the LORD, ‘so you have provoked Me to anger with the works of your hands.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Therefore this is what the LORD of Hosts says: ‘Because you have not obeyed My words,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"behold, I will summon all the families of the north, declares the LORD, and I will send for My servant Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, whom I will bring against this land, against its residents, and against all the surrounding nations. So I will devote them to destruction",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["25:9"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Forms of the Hebrew ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["cherem"]}," refer to the giving over of things or persons, either by destroying them or by giving them as an offering."]}],"caller":"+"},"and make them an object of horror and contempt, an everlasting desolation."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Moreover, I will banish from them the sounds of joy and gladness, the voices of the bride and bridegroom, the sound of the millstones, and the light of the lamp.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"And this whole land will become a desolate wasteland, and these nations will serve the king of Babylon for seventy years."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"But when seventy years are complete, I will punish the king of Babylon and that nation, the land of the Chaldeans,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["25:12"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, the Babylonians"]}],"caller":"+"},"for their guilt, declares the LORD, and I will make it an everlasting desolation."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"I will bring upon that land all the words I have pronounced against it, all that is written in this book, which Jeremiah has prophesied against all the nations.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"For many nations and great kings will enslave them, and I will repay them according to their deeds and according to the work of their hands.’”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Cup of God’s Wrath"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"This is what the LORD, the God of Israel, said to me: “Take from My hand this cup of the wine of wrath, and make all the nations to whom I send you drink from it.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"And they will drink and stagger and go out of their minds, because of the sword that I will send among them.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"So I took the cup from the LORD’s hand and made all the nations drink from it, each one to whom the LORD had sent me,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"to make them a ruin, an object of horror and contempt and cursing, as they are to this day—Jerusalem and the cities of Judah, its kings and officials;",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Pharaoh king of Egypt, his officials, his leaders, and all his people;",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"all the mixed tribes; all the kings of Uz; all the kings of the Philistines: Ashkelon, Gaza, Ekron, and the remnant of Ashdod;",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Edom, Moab, and the Ammonites;",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"all the kings of Tyre and Sidon; the kings of the coastlands across the sea;",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Dedan, Tema, Buz, and all who cut the corners of their hair;",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"all the kings of Arabia, and all the kings of the mixed tribes who dwell in the desert;",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"all the kings of Zimri, Elam, and Media;",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"all the kings of the north, both near and far, one after another—all the kingdoms on the face of the earth. And after all of them, the king of Sheshach",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["25:26"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Sheshach"]}," is a code name for Babylon."]}],"caller":"+"},"will drink it too."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"“Then you are to tell them that this is what the LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel, says: ‘Drink, get drunk, and vomit. Fall down and never get up again, because of the sword I will send among you.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"If they refuse to take the cup from your hand and drink it, you are to tell them that this is what the LORD of Hosts says: ‘You most certainly must drink it!",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"For behold, I am beginning to bring disaster on the city that bears My Name, so how could you possibly go unpunished? You will not go unpunished, for I am calling down a sword upon all the inhabitants of the earth, declares the LORD of Hosts.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"So you are to prophesy all these words against them and say to them:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘The LORD will roar from on high;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He will raise His voice from His holy habitation."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["He will roar loudly over His pasture;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like those who tread the grapes,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["He will call out with a shout"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["against all the inhabitants of the earth."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"The tumult will resound to the ends of the earth"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because the LORD brings a charge against the nations."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["He brings judgment on all mankind"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and puts the wicked to the sword,’”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"This is what the LORD of Hosts says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Behold! Disaster is spreading"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from nation to nation;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["a mighty storm is rising"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from the ends of the earth.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"Those slain by the LORD on that day will be spread from one end of the earth to the other. They will not be mourned, gathered, or buried. They will be like dung lying on the ground."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Cry of the Shepherds"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"Wail, you shepherds, and cry out;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["roll in the dust, you leaders of the flock."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For the days of your slaughter have come;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["you will fall and be shattered like fine pottery.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["25:34"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew; LXX ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["you will fall like the best of the rams"]},""]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"Flight will evade the shepherds,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and escape will elude the leaders of the flock."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"Hear the cry of the shepherds,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the wailing of the leaders of the flock,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the LORD is destroying their pasture."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"The peaceful meadows have been silenced"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because of the LORD’s burning anger."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"He has left His den like a lion,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for their land has been made a desolation"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["by the sword",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["25:38"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Some Hebrew manuscripts and LXX (see also",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Jeremiah 46:16"]},"and",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Jeremiah 50:16"]},"); most Hebrew manuscripts ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["anger"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"of the oppressor,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and because of the fierce anger of the LORD."]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"26"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["A Warning to the Cities of Judah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"At the beginning of the reign of Jehoiakim son of Josiah king of Judah, this word came from the LORD:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"“This is what the LORD says: Stand in the courtyard of the house of the LORD and speak all the words I have commanded you to speak to all the cities of Judah who come to worship there. Do not omit a word.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Perhaps they will listen and turn—each from his evil way of life—so that I may relent of the disaster I am planning to bring upon them because of the evil of their deeds."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"And you are to tell them that this is what the LORD says: ‘If you do not listen to Me and walk in My law, which I have set before you,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"and if you do not listen to the words of My servants the prophets, whom I have sent you again and again",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["26:5"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["I have sent you, rising up early and sending (them),"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"even though you did not listen,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"then I will make this house like Shiloh, and I will make this city an object of cursing among all the nations of the earth.’”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jeremiah Threatened with Death"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Now the priests and prophets and all the people heard Jeremiah speaking these words in the house of the LORD,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"and as soon as he had finished telling all the people everything the LORD had commanded him to say, the priests and prophets and all the people seized him, shouting, “You must surely die!",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"How dare you prophesy in the name of the LORD that this house will become like Shiloh and this city will be desolate and deserted!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["And all the people assembled against Jeremiah in the house of the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"When the officials of Judah heard these things, they went up from the king’s palace to the house of the LORD and sat there at the entrance of the New Gate."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Then the priests and prophets said to the officials and all the people, “This man is worthy of death, for he has prophesied against this city, as you have heard with your own ears!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"But Jeremiah said to all the officials and all the people, “The LORD sent me to prophesy against this house and against this city all the words that you have heard.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"So now, correct your ways and deeds, and obey the voice of the LORD your God, so that He might relent of the disaster He has pronounced against you.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"As for me, here I am in your hands; do to me what you think is good and right.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"But know for certain that if you put me to death, you will bring innocent blood upon yourselves, upon this city, and upon its residents; for truly the LORD has sent me to speak all these words in your hearing.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jeremiah Spared from Death"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Then the officials and all the people told the priests and prophets, “This man is not worthy of death, for he has spoken to us in the name of the LORD our God!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Some of the elders of the land stood up and said to the whole assembly of the people,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"“Micah the Moreshite prophesied in the days of Hezekiah king of Judah and told all the people of Judah that this is what the LORD of Hosts says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘Zion will be plowed like a field,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Jerusalem will become a heap of rubble,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the temple mount a wooded ridge.’",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["26:18"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Micah 3:12"]}]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Did Hezekiah king of Judah or anyone else in Judah put him to death? Did Hezekiah not fear the LORD and seek His favor, and did not the LORD relent of the disaster He had pronounced against them? But we are about to bring great harm on ourselves!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Prophet Uriah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Now there was another man prophesying in the name of the LORD, Uriah son of Shemaiah from Kiriath-jearim. He prophesied against this city and against this land the same things that Jeremiah did.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["26:20"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["according to all the words of Jeremiah"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"King Jehoiakim and all his mighty men and officials heard his words, and the king sought to put him to death. But when Uriah found out about it, he fled in fear and went to Egypt."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Then King Jehoiakim sent men to Egypt: Elnathan son of Achbor along with some other men.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"They brought Uriah out of Egypt and took him to King Jehoiakim, who had him put to the sword and his body thrown into the burial place of the common people."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Nevertheless, Ahikam son of Shaphan supported Jeremiah, so he was not handed over to the people to be put to death."]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"27"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Yoke of Nebuchadnezzar"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"At the beginning of the reign of Zedekiah",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["27:1"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A few Hebrew manuscripts and Syriac (see also verses 3 and 12, and",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Jeremiah 28:1"]},"); most Hebrew manuscripts ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Jehoiakim"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"son of Josiah king of Judah, this word came to Jeremiah from the LORD.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["27:1"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Most LXX manuscripts do not include this verse."]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"This is what the LORD said to me:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Make for yourself a yoke out of leather straps and put it on your neck.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Send word to the kings of Edom, Moab, Ammon, Tyre, and Sidon through the envoys who have come to Jerusalem to Zedekiah king of Judah.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Give them a message from the LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel, to relay to their masters:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"By My great power and outstretched arm, I made the earth and the men and beasts on the face of it, and I give it to whom I please.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"So now I have placed all these lands under the authority of My servant Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon. I have even made the beasts of the field subject to him.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"All nations will serve him and his son and grandson, until the time of his own land comes; then many nations and great kings will enslave him."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"As for the nation or kingdom that does not serve Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon and does not place its neck under his yoke, I will punish that nation by sword and famine and plague, declares the LORD, until I have destroyed it by his hand."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"But as for you, do not listen to your prophets, your diviners, your interpreters of dreams, your mediums, or your sorcerers who declare, ‘You will not serve the king of Babylon.’",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"For they prophesy to you a lie that will serve to remove you from your land; I will banish you and you will perish.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"But the nation that will put its neck under the yoke of the king of Babylon and serve him, I will leave in its own land, to cultivate it and reside in it, declares the LORD.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"And to Zedekiah king of Judah I spoke the same message: “Put your necks under the yoke of the king of Babylon; serve him and his people, and live!",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Why should you and your people die by sword and famine and plague, as the LORD has decreed against any nation that does not serve the king of Babylon?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Do not listen to the words of the prophets who say, ‘You must not serve the king of Babylon,’ for they are prophesying to you a lie.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"For I have not sent them, declares the LORD, and yet they are prophesying falsely in My name; therefore I will banish you, and you will perish—you and the prophets who prophesy to you.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Then I said to the priests and to all this people, “This is what the LORD says: Do not listen to the words of your prophets who prophesy to you, saying, ‘Look, very soon now the articles from the house of the LORD will be brought back from Babylon.’ They are prophesying to you a lie.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Do not listen to them. Serve the king of Babylon and live! Why should this city become a ruin?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"If they are indeed prophets and the word of the LORD is with them, let them now plead with the LORD of Hosts that the articles remaining in the house of the LORD, in the palace of the king of Judah, and in Jerusalem, not be taken to Babylon."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"For this is what the LORD of Hosts says about the pillars, the sea, the bases, and the rest of the articles that remain in this city,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"which Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon did not take when he carried Jeconiah",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["27:20"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Jeconiah"]}," is a variant of ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Jehoiachin"]},"; see",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["2 Kings 24:12"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"son of Jehoiakim king of Judah into exile from Jerusalem to Babylon, along with all the nobles of Judah and Jerusalem.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Yes, this is what the LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel, says about the articles that remain in the house of the LORD, in the palace of the king of Judah, and in Jerusalem:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"‘They will be carried to Babylon and will remain there until the day I attend to them again,’ declares the LORD. ‘Then I will bring them back and restore them to this place.’”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"28"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Hananiah’s False Prophecy"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"In the fifth month of that same year, the fourth year, near the beginning of the reign of King Zedekiah of Judah, the prophet Hananiah son of Azzur, who was from Gibeon, said to me in the house of the LORD in the presence of the priests and all the people:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"“This is what the LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel, says: ‘I have broken the yoke of the king of Babylon.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Within two years I will restore to this place all the articles of the house of the LORD that Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon removed from here and carried to Babylon.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"And I will restore to this place Jeconiah",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["28:4"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Jeconiah"]}," is a variant of ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Jehoiachin"]},"; see",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["2 Kings 24:12"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"son of Jehoiakim king of Judah, along with all the exiles from Judah who went to Babylon,’ declares the LORD, ‘for I will break the yoke of the king of Babylon.’”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Then the prophet Jeremiah replied to the prophet Hananiah in the presence of the priests and all the people who were standing in the house of the LORD.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"“Amen!” Jeremiah said. “May the LORD do so! May the LORD fulfill the words you have prophesied, and may He restore the articles of His house and all the exiles back to this place from Babylon."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Nevertheless, listen now to this message I am speaking in your hearing and in the hearing of all the people.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"The prophets of old who preceded you and me prophesied war, disaster, and plague against many lands and great kingdoms.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"As for the prophet who prophesies peace, only if the word of the prophet comes true will the prophet be recognized as one the LORD has truly sent.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Then the prophet Hananiah took the yoke off the neck of Jeremiah the prophet and broke it.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"And in the presence of all the people Hananiah proclaimed, “This is what the LORD says: ‘In this way, within two years I will break the yoke of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon off the neck of all the nations.’”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["At this, Jeremiah the prophet went on his way.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"But shortly after Hananiah the prophet had broken the yoke off his neck, the word of the LORD came to Jeremiah:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"“Go and tell Hananiah that this is what the LORD says: ‘You have broken a yoke of wood, but in its place you have fashioned a yoke of iron.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"For this is what the LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel, says: ‘I have put a yoke of iron on the neck of all these nations to make them serve Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, and they will serve him. I have even given him control of the beasts of the field.’”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Then the prophet Jeremiah said to the prophet Hananiah, “Listen, Hananiah! The LORD did not send you, but you have persuaded this people to trust in a lie.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Therefore this is what the LORD says: ‘I am about to remove you from the face of the earth. You will die this year because you have preached rebellion against the LORD.’”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"And in the seventh month of that very year, the prophet Hananiah died."]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"29"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jeremiah’s Letter to the Exiles"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"This is the text of the letter that Jeremiah the prophet sent from Jerusalem to the surviving elders among the exiles and to the priests, the prophets, and all the others Nebuchadnezzar had carried into exile from Jerusalem to Babylon.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"(This was after King Jeconiah,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["29:2"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Jeconiah"]}," is a variant of ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Jehoiachin"]},"; see",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["2 Kings 24:12"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"the queen mother, the court officials, the officials of Judah and Jerusalem, the craftsmen, and the metalsmiths had been exiled from Jerusalem.)",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"The letter was entrusted to Elasah son of Shaphan and Gemariah son of Hilkiah, whom Zedekiah king of Judah sent to King Nebuchadnezzar in Babylon. It stated:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"This is what the LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel, says to all the exiles who were carried away from Jerusalem to Babylon:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"“Build houses and settle down. Plant gardens and eat their produce.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Take wives and have sons and daughters. Take wives for your sons and give your daughters in marriage, so that they too may have sons and daughters. Multiply there; do not decrease.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Seek the prosperity of the city to which I have sent you as exiles. Pray to the LORD on its behalf, for if it prospers, you too will prosper.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"For this is what the LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel, says: “Do not be deceived by the prophets and diviners among you, and do not listen to the dreams you elicit from them.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"For they are falsely prophesying to you in My name; I have not sent them, declares the LORD.”",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["29:9"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Some translators close the written portion of this letter later in the chapter."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"For this is what the LORD says: “When Babylon’s seventy years are complete, I will attend to you and confirm My promise to restore you to this place.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"For I know the plans I have for you, declares the LORD, plans to prosper you and not to harm you, to give you a future and a hope.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Then you will call upon Me and come and pray to Me, and I will listen to you.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"You will seek Me and find Me when you search for Me with all your heart.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"I will be found by you, declares the LORD, and I will restore you from captivity",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["29:14"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["restore your fortunes"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"and gather you from all the nations and places to which I have banished you, declares the LORD. I will restore you to the place from which I sent you into exile.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Because you may say, “The LORD has raised up for us prophets in Babylon,”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"this is what the LORD says about the king who sits on David’s throne and all the people who remain in this city, your brothers who did not go with you into exile—",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"this is what the LORD of Hosts says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“I will send against them sword and famine and plague, and I will make them like rotten figs, so bad they cannot be eaten.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"I will pursue them with sword and famine and plague. I will make them a horror to all the kingdoms of the earth—a curse, a desolation, and an object of scorn and reproach among all the nations to which I banish them.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"I will do this because they have not listened to My words, declares the LORD, which I sent to them again and again",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["29:19"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["I sent to them, rising up early and sending (to them)"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"through My servants the prophets. And neither have you exiles listened, declares the LORD.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"So hear the word of the LORD, all you exiles I have sent away from Jerusalem to Babylon.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"This is what the LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel, says about Ahab son of Kolaiah and Zedekiah son of Maaseiah, who are prophesying to you lies in My name: “I will deliver them to Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, and he will kill them before your very eyes.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Because of them, all the exiles of Judah who are in Babylon will use this curse: ‘May the LORD make you like Zedekiah and Ahab, whom the king of Babylon roasted in the fire!’",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"For they have committed an outrage in Israel by committing adultery with the wives of their neighbors and speaking lies in My name, which I did not command them to do. I am He who knows, and I am a witness, declares the LORD.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Message to Shemaiah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"You are to tell Shemaiah the Nehelamite that",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"this is what the LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel, says: “In your own name you have sent out letters to all the people of Jerusalem, to the priest Zephaniah son of Maaseiah, and to all the priests. You said to Zephaniah:",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["29:25"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["You said"]},"; the addressee ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Zephaniah"]}," is added for clarity."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"‘The LORD has appointed you priest in place of Jehoiada, to be the chief officer in the house of the LORD, responsible for any madman who acts like a prophet—you must put him in stocks and neck irons.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"So now, why have you not rebuked Jeremiah of Anathoth, who poses as a prophet among you?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"For he has sent to us in Babylon, claiming: Since the exile will be lengthy, build houses and settle down; plant gardens and eat their produce.’”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"(Zephaniah the priest, however, had read this letter to Jeremiah the prophet.)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"Then the word of the LORD came to Jeremiah:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"“Send a message telling all the exiles what the LORD says concerning Shemaiah the Nehelamite. Because Shemaiah has prophesied to you—though I did not send him—and has made you trust in a lie,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"this is what the LORD says: ‘ I will surely punish Shemaiah the Nehelamite and his descendants. He will have no one left among this people, nor will he see the good that I will bring to My people, declares the LORD, for he has preached rebellion against the LORD.’”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"30"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Restoration of Israel and Judah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Ezekiel 28:25–26)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"This is the word that came to Jeremiah from the LORD:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"“This is what the LORD, the God of Israel, says: ‘Write in a book all the words that I have spoken to you.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"For behold, the days are coming, declares the LORD, when I will restore from captivity",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["30:3"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["restore the fortunes of"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"My people Israel and Judah, declares the LORD. I will restore them to the land that I gave to their fathers, and they will possess it.’”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"These are the words that the LORD spoke concerning Israel and Judah.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Yes, this is what the LORD says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“A cry of panic is heard—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a cry of terror, not of peace."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Ask now, and see:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Can a male give birth?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Why then do I see every man"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with his hands on his stomach like a woman in labor"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and every face turned pale?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"How awful that day will be!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["None will be like it!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["It is the time of Jacob’s distress,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but he will be saved out of it."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"On that day,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["declares the LORD of Hosts,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will break the yoke off their necks"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and tear off their bonds,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and no longer will strangers enslave them."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Instead, they will serve the LORD their God"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and David their king,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["whom I will raise up for them."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"As for you, O Jacob My servant, do not be afraid,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["declares the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and do not be dismayed,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["O Israel."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For I will surely save you out of a distant place,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["your descendants from the land of their captivity!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Jacob will return to quiet and ease,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with no one to make him afraid."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"For I am with you to save you,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Though I will completely destroy all the nations to which I have scattered you,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will not completely destroy you."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Yet I will discipline you justly,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will by no means leave you unpunished.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"For this is what the LORD says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Your injury is incurable;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["your wound is grievous."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"There is no one to plead your cause,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["no remedy for your sores,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["no recovery for you."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"All your lovers have forgotten you;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they no longer seek you,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for I have struck you as an enemy would,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with the discipline of someone cruel,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["because of your great iniquity"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and your numerous sins."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Why do you cry out over your wound?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Your pain has no cure!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Because of your great iniquity"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and your numerous sins"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I have done these things to you."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Nevertheless, all who devour you will be devoured,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and all your adversaries—every one of them—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["will go off into exile."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Those who plundered you will be plundered,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and all who raided you will be raided."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"But I will restore your health and heal your wounds,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["declares the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["because they call you an outcast,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Zion, for whom no one cares.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"This is what the LORD says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“I will restore the fortunes of",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["30:18"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["restore from captivity"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"Jacob’s tents"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and have compassion on his dwellings."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["And the city will be rebuilt on her own ruins,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the palace will stand in its rightful place."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Thanksgiving will proceed from them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a sound of celebration."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will multiply them, and they will not be decreased;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will honor them, and they will not be belittled."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Their children will be as in days of old,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and their congregation will be established before Me;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and I will punish all their oppressors."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Their leader will be one of their own,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and their ruler will arise from their midst."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["And I will bring him near, and he will approach Me,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for who would dare on his own to approach Me?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"“And you will be My people,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and I will be your God.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Behold, the storm of the LORD"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["has gone out with fury,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["a whirlwind swirling down"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["upon the heads of the wicked."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"The fierce anger of the LORD will not turn back"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["until He has fully accomplished the purposes of His heart."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["In the days to come"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["you will understand this."]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"31"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Mourning Turned to Joy"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 2:16–18)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"“At that time,” declares the LORD, “I will be the God of all the families of Israel, and they will be My people.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"This is what the LORD says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“The people who survived the sword"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["found favor in the wilderness"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["when Israel went to find rest.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"The LORD appeared to us in the past, saying:",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["31:3"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["The LORD appeared to him from afar, saying"]},""]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“I have loved you with an everlasting love;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["therefore I have drawn you with loving devotion."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Again I will build you, and you will be rebuilt,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["O Virgin Israel."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Again you will take up your tambourines"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and go out in joyful dancing."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Again you will plant vineyards on the hills of Samaria;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the farmers will plant and enjoy the fruit."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"For there will be a day when watchmen will call out"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["on the hills of Ephraim,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘Arise, let us go up to Zion,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to the LORD our God!’”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"For this is what the LORD says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Sing with joy for Jacob;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["shout for the foremost of the nations!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Make your praises heard, and say,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘O LORD, save Your people,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the remnant of Israel!’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Behold, I will bring them from the land of the north"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and gather them from the farthest parts of the earth,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["including the blind and the lame,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["expectant mothers and women in labor."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They will return as a great assembly!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"They will come with weeping,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and by their supplication I will lead them;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will make them walk beside streams of waters,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["on a level path where they will not stumble."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For I am Israel’s Father,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and Ephraim is My firstborn.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Hear, O nations, the word of the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and proclaim it in distant coastlands:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“The One who scattered Israel will gather them and keep them"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["as a shepherd keeps his flock."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"For the LORD has ransomed Jacob"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and redeemed him from the hand that had overpowered him."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"They will come and shout for joy on the heights of Zion;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they will be radiant over the bounty of the LORD—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["the grain, new wine, and oil,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the young of the flocks and herds."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Their life will be like a well-watered garden,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and never again will they languish."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Then the maidens will rejoice with dancing,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["young men and old as well."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will turn their mourning into joy,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and give them comfort and joy for their sorrow."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"I will fill the souls of the priests abundantly,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will fill My people with My goodness,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"This is what the LORD says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“A voice is heard in Ramah,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["mourning and great weeping,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Rachel weeping for her children"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and refusing to be comforted,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because they are no more.”",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["31:15"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Cited in",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Matthew 2:18"]}]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"This is what the LORD says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Keep your voice from weeping"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and your eyes from tears,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for the reward for your work will come,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Then your children will return"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from the land of the enemy."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"So there is hope for your future,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["declares the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and your children will return"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to their own land."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"I have surely heard Ephraim’s",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["31:18"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, the northern kingdom of Israel; also in verse 20"]}],"caller":"+"},"moaning:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘You disciplined me severely,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like an untrained calf."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Restore me, that I may return,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for You are the LORD my God."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"After I returned, I repented;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and after I was instructed, I struck my thigh in grief."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I was ashamed and humiliated"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because I bore the disgrace of my youth.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Is not Ephraim a precious son to Me,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a delightful child?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Though I often speak against him,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I still remember him."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Therefore My heart yearns for him;",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["31:20"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["My bowels yearn for him"]},""]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I have great compassion for him,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"“Set up the road markers,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["put up the signposts."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Keep the highway in mind,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the road you have traveled."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Return, O Virgin Israel,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["return to these cities of yours."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"How long will you wander,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["O faithless daughter?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For the LORD has created a new thing in the land—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a woman will shelter",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["31:22"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["will surround"]}," or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["will return to"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"a man.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"This is what the LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel, says: “When I restore them from captivity,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["31:23"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["restore their fortunes"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"they will once again speak this word in the land of Judah and in its cities: ‘May the LORD bless you, O righteous dwelling place, O holy mountain.’",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"And Judah and all its cities will dwell together in the land, the farmers and those who move with the flocks,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"for I will refresh the weary soul and replenish all who are weak.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The New Covenant"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Hebrews 8:6–13)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"At this I awoke and looked around. My sleep had been most pleasant to me."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"“The days are coming,” declares the LORD, “when I will sow the house of Israel and the house of Judah with the seed of man and of beast.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"Just as I watched over them to uproot and tear down, to demolish, destroy, and bring disaster, so I will watch over them to build and to plant,” declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"“In those days, it will no longer be said:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘The fathers have eaten sour grapes,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the teeth of the children are set on edge.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"Instead, each will die for his own iniquity. If anyone eats the sour grapes, his own teeth will be set on edge."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"Behold, the days are coming, declares the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["when I will make a new covenant"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["with the house of Israel"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and with the house of Judah."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"It will not be like the covenant"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I made with their fathers"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["when I took them by the hand"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to lead them out of the land of Egypt—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["a covenant they broke,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["though I was a husband to them,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["31:32"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew; LXX ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["for they did not abide in My covenant, and I disregarded them"]},"; see also Syriac."]}],"caller":"+"},"”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"“But this is the covenant I will make with the house of Israel"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["after those days, declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will put My law in their minds"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and inscribe it on their hearts."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["And I will be their God,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they will be My people."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"No longer will each man teach his neighbor or his brother,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["saying, ‘Know the LORD,’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["because they will all know Me,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from the least of them to the greatest, declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For I will forgive their iniquities"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will remember their sins no more.”",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["31:34"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Cited in",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Hebrews 8:8–12"]},"and",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Hebrews 10:16–17"]}]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"Thus says the LORD, who gives the sun for light by day, who sets in order the moon and stars for light by night, who stirs up the sea so that its waves roar—the LORD of Hosts is His name:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"“Only if this fixed order departed from My presence,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["declares the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["would Israel’s descendants ever cease"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to be a nation before Me.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"This is what the LORD says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Only if the heavens above could be measured"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the foundations of the earth below searched out"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["would I reject all of Israel’s descendants"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because of all they have done,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"“The days are coming,”",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["31:38"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["Behold, the days"]},"; alternate MT reading ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Behold, the days are coming"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"declares the LORD, “when this city will be rebuilt for Me, from the tower of Hananel to the Corner Gate.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"The measuring line will once again stretch out straight to the hill of Gareb and then turn toward Goah.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40"},"The whole valley of the dead bodies and ashes, and all the fields as far as the Kidron Valley, to the corner of the Horse Gate to the east, will be holy to the LORD. It will never again be uprooted or demolished.”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"32"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jeremiah Buys Hanamel’s Field"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"This is the word that came to Jeremiah from the LORD in the tenth year of Zedekiah king of Judah, which was the eighteenth year of Nebuchadnezzar.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"At that time the army of the king of Babylon was besieging Jerusalem, and Jeremiah the prophet was imprisoned in the courtyard of the guard, which was in the palace of the king of Judah."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"For Zedekiah king of Judah had imprisoned him, saying: “Why are you prophesying like this? You claim that the LORD says, ‘Behold, I am about to deliver this city into the hand of the king of Babylon, and he will capture it.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Zedekiah king of Judah will not escape from the hands of the Chaldeans,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["32:4"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, the Babylonians; also in verses 5, 24, 25, 28, 29, and 43"]}],"caller":"+"},"but he will surely be delivered into the hand of the king of Babylon, and will speak with him face to face and see him eye to eye.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"He will take Zedekiah to Babylon, where he will stay until I attend to him, declares the LORD. If you fight against the Chaldeans, you will not succeed.’”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Jeremiah replied, “The word of the LORD came to me, saying:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Behold! Hanamel, the son of your uncle Shallum, is coming to you to say, ‘Buy for yourself my field in Anathoth, for you have the right of redemption to buy it.’",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Then, as the LORD had said, my cousin Hanamel came to me in the courtyard of the guard and urged me, ‘Please buy my field in Anathoth in the land of Benjamin, for you own the right of inheritance and redemption. Buy it for yourself.’”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Then I knew that this was the word of the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"So I bought the field in Anathoth from my cousin Hanamel, and I weighed out seventeen shekels of silver.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["32:9"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["17 shekels"]}," is approximately 6.8 ounces or 193.8 grams of silver."]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"I signed and sealed the deed, called in witnesses, and weighed out the silver on the scales.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Then I took the deed of purchase—the sealed copy with its terms and conditions, as well as the open copy—",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"and I gave this deed to Baruch son of Neriah, the son of Mahseiah, in the sight of my cousin Hanamel and the witnesses who were signing the purchase agreement and all the Jews sitting in the courtyard of the guard."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"In their sight I instructed Baruch,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"“This is what the LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel, says: Take these deeds—both the sealed copy and the open copy of the deed of purchase—and put them in a clay jar to preserve them for a long time.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"For this is what the LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel, says: Houses, fields, and vineyards will again be bought in this land.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jeremiah Prays for Understanding"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"After I had given the deed of purchase to Baruch son of Neriah, I prayed to the LORD:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"“Oh, Lord GOD! You have made the heavens and the earth by Your great power and outstretched arm. Nothing is too difficult for You!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"You show loving devotion to thousands but lay the iniquity of the fathers into the laps",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["32:18"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["into the bosom"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"of their children after them, O great and mighty God whose name is the LORD of Hosts,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"the One great in counsel and mighty in deed, whose eyes are on all the ways of the sons of men, to reward each one according to his ways and according to the fruit of his deeds."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"You performed signs and wonders in the land of Egypt, and You do so to this very day, both in Israel and among all mankind. And You have made a name for Yourself, as is the case to this day."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"You brought Your people Israel out of the land of Egypt with signs and wonders, with a strong hand and an outstretched arm, and with great terror.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"You gave them this land that You had sworn to give their fathers, a land flowing with milk and honey."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"They came in and possessed it, but they did not obey Your voice or walk in Your law. They failed to perform all that You commanded them to do, and so You have brought upon them all this disaster.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"See how the siege ramps are mounted against the city to capture it. And by sword and famine and plague, the city has been given into the hands of the Chaldeans who are fighting against it. What You have spoken has happened, as You now see!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"Yet You, O Lord GOD, have said to me, ‘Buy for yourself the field with silver and call in witnesses, even though the city has been delivered into the hands of the Chaldeans!’”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The LORD Answers Jeremiah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"Then the word of the LORD came to Jeremiah:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"“Behold, I am the LORD, the God of all flesh. Is anything too difficult for Me?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"Therefore this is what the LORD says: Behold, I am about to deliver this city into the hands of the Chaldeans and of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, who will capture it.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"And the Chaldeans who are fighting against this city will come in, set it on fire, and burn it, along with the houses of those who provoked Me to anger by burning incense to Baal on their rooftops and by pouring out drink offerings to other gods."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"For the children of Israel and of Judah have done nothing but evil in My sight from their youth; indeed, they have done nothing but provoke Me to anger by the work of their hands, declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"For this city has aroused My wrath and fury from the day it was built until now. Therefore I will remove it from My presence",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"because of all the evil the children of Israel and of Judah have done to provoke Me to anger—they, their kings, their officials, their priests and prophets, the men of Judah, and the residents of Jerusalem.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"They have turned their backs to Me and not their faces. Though I taught them again and again,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["32:33"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["I taught them, rising up early and teaching,"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"they would not listen or respond to discipline."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"They have placed their abominations in the house that bears My Name, and so have defiled it.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"They have built the high places of Baal in the Valley of Ben-hinnom to make their sons and daughters pass through the fire to Molech—something I never commanded them, nor had it ever entered My mind, that they should commit such an abomination and cause Judah to sin."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["A Promise of Restoration"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Ezekiel 11:13–21)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"Now therefore, about this city of which you say, ‘It will be delivered into the hand of the king of Babylon by sword and famine and plague,’ this is what the LORD, the God of Israel, says:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"I will surely gather My people from all the lands to which I have banished them in My furious anger and great wrath, and I will return them to this place and make them dwell in safety.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"They will be My people, and I will be their God.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["32:38"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Cited in",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["2 Corinthians 6:16"]}]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"I will give them one heart and one way, so that they will always fear Me for their own good and for the good of their children after them."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40"},"I will make an everlasting covenant with them: I will never turn away from doing good to them, and I will put My fear in their hearts, so that they will never turn away from Me.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41"},"Yes, I will rejoice in doing them good, and I will faithfully plant them in this land with all My heart and with all My soul."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42"},"For this is what the LORD says: Just as I have brought all this great disaster on this people, so I will bring on them all the good I have promised them.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43"},"And fields will be bought in this land about which you are saying, ‘It is a desolation, without man or beast; it has been delivered into the hands of the Chaldeans.’",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44"},"Fields will be purchased with silver, and deeds will be signed, sealed, and witnessed in the land of Benjamin, in the areas surrounding Jerusalem, and in the cities of Judah—the cities of the hill country, the foothills,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["32:44"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Shephelah"]}," or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["lowlands"]},"; that is, the western foothills of Judea"]}],"caller":"+"},"and the Negev—because I will restore them from captivity,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["32:44"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["restore their fortunes"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"declares the LORD.”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"33"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Excellence of the Restored Nation"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"While Jeremiah was still confined in the courtyard of the guard, the word of the LORD came to him a second time:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"“Thus says the LORD who made the earth,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["33:2"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["LXX; Hebrew ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["who made it"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"the LORD who formed it and established it, the LORD is His name:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Call to Me, and I will answer and show you great and unsearchable things you do not know."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"For this is what the LORD, the God of Israel, says about the houses of this city and the palaces of the kings of Judah that have been torn down for defense against the siege ramps and the sword:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"The Chaldeans are coming to fight",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["33:5"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["They are coming to fight the Chaldeans"]},"; that is, the Babylonians"]}],"caller":"+"},"and to fill those places with the corpses of the men I will strike down in My anger and in My wrath. I have hidden My face from this city because of all its wickedness."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Nevertheless, I will bring to it health and healing, and I will heal its people and reveal to them the abundance of peace and truth.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"I will restore Judah and Israel from captivity",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["33:7"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["restore the fortunes of Judah and Israel"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"and will rebuild them as in former times.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"And I will cleanse them from all the iniquity they have committed against Me, and will forgive all their sins of rebellion against Me."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"So this city will bring Me renown, joy, praise, and glory before all the nations of the earth, who will hear of all the good I do for it. They will tremble in awe because of all the goodness and prosperity that I will provide for it."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"This is what the LORD says: In this place you say is a wasteland without man or beast, in the cities of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem that are deserted—inhabited by neither man nor beast—there will be heard again",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"the sounds of joy and gladness, the voices of the bride and bridegroom, and the voices of those bringing thank offerings into the house of the LORD, saying:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘Give thanks to the LORD of Hosts,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the LORD is good;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["His loving devotion endures forever.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["For I will restore the land from captivity",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["33:11"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["restore the fortunes of the land"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"as in former times, says the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"This is what the LORD of Hosts says: In this desolate place, without man or beast, and in all its cities, there will once more be pastures for shepherds to rest their flocks.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"In the cities of the hill country, the foothills,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["33:13"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Shephelah"]}," or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["lowlands"]},"; that is, the western foothills of Judea"]}],"caller":"+"},"and the Negev, in the land of Benjamin and the cities surrounding Jerusalem, and in the cities of Judah, the flocks will again pass under the hands of the one who counts them, says the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Covenant with David"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Behold, the days are coming,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["declares the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["when I will fulfill the gracious promise"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that I have spoken"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["to the house of Israel"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the house of Judah."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"In those days and at that time"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will cause to sprout for David a righteous Branch,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and He will administer justice"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and righteousness in the land."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"In those days Judah will be saved,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and Jerusalem will dwell securely,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and this is the name by which it will be called:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The LORD Our Righteousness.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["33:16"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["YHWH Tsidqenu"]},""]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"For this is what the LORD says: David will never lack a man to sit on the throne of the house of Israel,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"nor will the priests who are Levites ever fail to have a man before Me to offer burnt offerings, to burn grain offerings, and to present sacrifices.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"And the word of the LORD came to Jeremiah:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"“This is what the LORD says: If you can break My covenant with the day and My covenant with the night, so that day and night cease to occupy their appointed time,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"then My covenant may also be broken with David My servant and with My ministers the Levites who are priests, so that David will not have a son to reign on his throne.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"As the hosts of heaven cannot be counted and as the sand on the seashore cannot be measured, so too will I multiply the descendants of My servant David and the Levites who minister before Me.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Moreover, the word of the LORD came to Jeremiah:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"“Have you not noticed what these people are saying: ‘The LORD has rejected the two families He had chosen’? So they despise My people and no longer regard them as a nation.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"This is what the LORD says: If I have not established My covenant with the day and the night and the fixed order of heaven and earth,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"then I would also reject the descendants of Jacob and of My servant David, so as not to take from his descendants rulers over the descendants of Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob. For I will restore them from captivity",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["33:26"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["restore their fortunes"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"and will have compassion on them.”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"34"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["A Prophecy against Zedekiah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"This is the word that came to Jeremiah from the LORD when Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, all his army, all the earthly kingdoms under his control, and all the other nations were fighting against Jerusalem and all its surrounding cities.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"The LORD, the God of Israel, told Jeremiah to go and speak to Zedekiah king of Judah and tell him that this is what the LORD says: “Behold, I am about to deliver this city into the hand of the king of Babylon, and he will burn it down.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"And you yourself will not escape his grasp, but will surely be captured and delivered into his hand. You will see the king of Babylon eye to eye and speak with him face to face; and you will go to Babylon."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Yet hear the word of the LORD, O Zedekiah king of Judah. This is what the LORD says concerning you: You will not die by the sword;",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"you will die in peace. As spices were burned for your fathers, the former kings who preceded you, so people will burn spices for you and lament, ‘Alas, O master!’ For I Myself have spoken this word, declares the LORD.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"In Jerusalem, then, Jeremiah the prophet relayed all these words to Zedekiah king of Judah",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"as the army of the king of Babylon was fighting against Jerusalem and the remaining cities of Judah—against Lachish and Azekah. For these were the only fortified cities remaining in Judah."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Freedom for Hebrew Slaves"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"After King Zedekiah had made a covenant with all the people in Jerusalem to proclaim liberty, the word came to Jeremiah from the LORD",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"that each man should free his Hebrew slaves, both male and female, and no one should hold his fellow Jew in bondage.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"So all the officials and all the people who entered into this covenant agreed that they would free their menservants and maidservants and no longer hold them in bondage. They obeyed and released them,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"but later they changed their minds and took back the menservants and maidservants they had freed, and they forced them to become slaves again."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Then the word of the LORD came to Jeremiah from the LORD, saying,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"“This is what the LORD, the God of Israel, says: I made a covenant with your forefathers when I brought them out of the land of Egypt, out of the house of slavery, saying:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Every seventh year, each of you must free his Hebrew brother who has sold himself to you. He may serve you six years, but then you must let him go free. But your fathers did not listen or incline their ear."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Recently you repented and did what pleased Me; each of you proclaimed freedom for his neighbor. You made a covenant before Me in the house that bears My Name.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"But now you have changed your minds and profaned My name. Each of you has taken back the menservants and maidservants whom you had set at liberty to go wherever they wanted, and you have again forced them to be your slaves."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Therefore this is what the LORD says: You have not obeyed Me; you have not proclaimed freedom, each man for his brother and for his neighbor. So now I proclaim freedom for you, declares the LORD—freedom to fall by sword, by plague, and by famine! I will make you a horror to all the kingdoms of the earth."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"And those who have transgressed My covenant and have not fulfilled the terms of the covenant they made before Me, I will treat like the calf they cut in two in order to pass between its pieces.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"The officials of Judah and Jerusalem, the court officials, the priests, and all the people of the land who passed between the pieces of the calf,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"I will deliver into the hands of their enemies who seek their lives. Their corpses will become food for the birds of the air and the beasts of the earth.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"And I will deliver Zedekiah king of Judah and his officials into the hands of their enemies who seek their lives, to the army of the king of Babylon that had withdrawn from you."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Behold, I am going to give the command, declares the LORD, and I will bring them back to this city. They will fight against it, capture it, and burn it down. And I will make the cities of Judah a desolation, without inhabitant.”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"35"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Obedience of the Rechabites"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"This is the word that came to Jeremiah from the LORD in the days of Jehoiakim son of Josiah king of Judah:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"“Go to the house of the Rechabites, speak to them, and bring them to one of the chambers of the house of the LORD to offer them a drink of wine.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"So I took Jaazaniah son of Jeremiah, the son of Habazziniah, and his brothers and all his sons—the entire house of the Rechabites—",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"and I brought them into the house of the LORD, to a chamber occupied by the sons of Hanan son of Igdaliah, a man of God. This room was near the chamber of the officials, which was above the chamber of Maaseiah son of Shallum the doorkeeper."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Then I set pitchers full of wine and some cups before the men of the house of the Rechabites, and I said to them, “Drink some wine.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"“We do not drink wine,” they replied, “for our forefather Jonadab",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["35:6"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Jonadab"]}," is a variant of ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Jehonadab"]},"; here and throughout this chapter; see",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["2 Kings 10:15"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"son of Rechab commanded us, ‘Neither you nor your descendants are ever to drink wine.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Nor are you ever to build a house or sow seed or plant a vineyard. Those things are not for you. Instead, you must live in tents all your lives, so that you may live a long time in the land where you wander.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"And we have obeyed the voice of our forefather Jonadab son of Rechab in all he commanded us. So we have not drunk wine all our lives—neither we nor our wives nor our sons and daughters.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Nor have we built houses in which to live, and we have not owned any vineyards or fields or crops.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"But we have lived in tents and have obeyed and done exactly as our forefather Jonadab commanded us."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"So when Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon marched into the land, we said: ‘Come, let us go into Jerusalem to escape the armies of the Chaldeans",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["35:11"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, the Babylonians"]}],"caller":"+"},"and the Arameans.’ So we have remained in Jerusalem.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Judah Rebuked"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Then the word of the LORD came to Jeremiah:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"“This is what the LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel, says: Go and tell the men of Judah and the residents of Jerusalem: ‘Will you not accept discipline and obey My words?’ declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"The words of Jonadab son of Rechab have been carried out. He commanded his sons not to drink wine, and they have not drunk it to this very day because they have obeyed the command of their forefather. But I have spoken to you again and again,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["35:14"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["But I have spoken to you, rising up early and speaking,"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"and you have not obeyed Me!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Again and again I have sent you",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["35:15"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["Rising up early and sending (you), I have sent you"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"all My servants the prophets, proclaiming: ‘Turn now, each of you, from your wicked ways, and correct your actions. Do not go after other gods to serve them. Live in the land that I have given to you and your fathers.’ But you have not inclined your ear or listened to Me.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Yes, the sons of Jonadab son of Rechab carried out the command their forefather gave them, but these people have not listened to Me."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Therefore this is what the LORD God of Hosts, the God of Israel, says: ‘Behold, I will bring to Judah and to all the residents of Jerusalem all the disaster I have pronounced against them, because I have spoken to them but they have not obeyed, and I have called to them but they have not answered.’”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Then Jeremiah said to the house of the Rechabites: “This is what the LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel, says: ‘Because you have obeyed the command of your forefather Jonadab and have kept all his commandments and have done all that he charged you to do,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"this is what the LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel, says: Jonadab son of Rechab will never fail to have a man to stand before Me.’”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"36"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jeremiah’s Scroll Read in the Temple"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"In the fourth year of Jehoiakim son of Josiah king of Judah, this word came to Jeremiah from the LORD:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"“Take a scroll and write on it all the words I have spoken to you concerning Israel, Judah, and all the nations, from the day I first spoke to you during the reign of Josiah until today.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Perhaps when the people of Judah hear about all the calamity I plan to bring upon them, each of them will turn from his wicked way. Then I will forgive their iniquity and their sin.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"So Jeremiah called Baruch son of Neriah, and at the dictation of Jeremiah, Baruch wrote on a scroll all the words that the LORD had spoken to Jeremiah."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Then Jeremiah commanded Baruch, “I am restricted; I cannot enter the house of the LORD;",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"so you are to go to the house of the LORD on a day of fasting, and in the hearing of the people you are to read the words of the LORD from the scroll you have written at my dictation. Read them in the hearing of all the people of Judah who are coming from their cities."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Perhaps they will bring their petition before the LORD, and each one will turn from his wicked way; for great are the anger and fury that the LORD has pronounced against this people.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"So Baruch son of Neriah did everything that Jeremiah the prophet had commanded him. In the house of the LORD he read the words of the LORD from the scroll."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Now in the ninth month of the fifth year of Jehoiakim son of Josiah king of Judah, a fast before the LORD was proclaimed to all the people of Jerusalem and all who had come there from the cities of Judah.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"From the chamber of Gemariah son of Shaphan the scribe, which was in the upper courtyard at the opening of the New Gate of the house of the LORD, Baruch read from the scroll the words of Jeremiah in the hearing of all the people."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jeremiah’s Scroll Read in the Palace"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"When Micaiah son of Gemariah, the son of Shaphan, heard all the words of the LORD from the scroll,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"he went down to the scribe’s chamber in the king’s palace, where all the officials were sitting: Elishama the scribe, Delaiah son of Shemaiah, Elnathan son of Achbor, Gemariah son of Shaphan, Zedekiah son of Hananiah, and all the other officials.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"And Micaiah reported to them all the words he had heard Baruch read from the scroll in the hearing of the people."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Then all the officials sent word to Baruch through Jehudi son of Nethaniah, the son of Shelemiah, the son of Cushi, saying, “Bring the scroll that you read in the hearing of the people, and come here.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["So Baruch son of Neriah took the scroll and went to them."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"“Please sit down,” they said, “and read it in our hearing.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["So Baruch read it in their hearing."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"When they had heard all these words, they turned to one another in fear and said to Baruch, “Surely we must report all these words to the king.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"“Tell us now,” they asked Baruch, “how did you write all these words? Was it at Jeremiah’s dictation?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"“It was at his dictation,” Baruch replied. “He recited all these words to me and I wrote them in ink on the scroll.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Then the officials said to Baruch, “You and Jeremiah must hide yourselves and tell no one where you are.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jehoiakim Burns the Scroll"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"So the officials went to the king in the courtyard. And having stored the scroll in the chamber of Elishama the scribe, they reported everything to the king."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Then the king sent Jehudi to get the scroll, and he took it from the chamber of Elishama the scribe. And Jehudi read it in the hearing of the king and all the officials who were standing beside him."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Since it was the ninth month, the king was sitting in his winter quarters with a fire burning before him.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"And as soon as Jehudi had read three or four columns, Jehoiakim would cut them off with a scribe’s knife and throw them into the firepot, until the entire scroll had been consumed by the fire."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Yet in hearing all these words, the king and his servants did not become frightened or tear their garments.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"Even though Elnathan, Delaiah, and Gemariah urged the king not to burn the scroll, he would not listen to them.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"Instead, the king commanded Jerahmeel, a son of the king, as well as Seraiah son of Azriel and Shelemiah son of Abdeel, to seize Baruch the scribe and Jeremiah the prophet. But the LORD had hidden them."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jeremiah Rewrites the Scroll"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"After the king had burned the scroll containing the words that Baruch had written at Jeremiah’s dictation, the word of the LORD came to Jeremiah:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"“Take another scroll and rewrite on it the very words that were on the original scroll, which Jehoiakim king of Judah has burned."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"You are to proclaim concerning Jehoiakim king of Judah that this is what the LORD says: You have burned the scroll and said, ‘Why have you written on it that the king of Babylon would surely come and destroy this land and deprive it of man and beast?’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"Therefore this is what the LORD says about Jehoiakim king of Judah: He will have no one to sit on David’s throne, and his body will be thrown out and exposed to heat by day and frost by night.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"I will punish him and his descendants and servants for their iniquity. I will bring on them, on the residents of Jerusalem, and on the men of Judah, all the calamity about which I warned them but they did not listen.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"Then Jeremiah took another scroll and gave it to the scribe Baruch son of Neriah, and at Jeremiah’s dictation he wrote on it all the words of the scroll that Jehoiakim king of Judah had burned in the fire. And many similar words were added to them."]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"37"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jeremiah Warns Zedekiah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon made Zedekiah son of Josiah the king of Judah, and he reigned in place of Coniah",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["37:1"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Coniah"]}," is a variant of ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Jehoiachin"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"son of Jehoiakim.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"But he and his officers and the people of the land refused to obey the words that the LORD had spoken through Jeremiah the prophet."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Yet King Zedekiah sent Jehucal",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["37:3"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Jehucal"]}," is a variant of ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Jucal"]},"; see",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Jeremiah 38:1"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"son of Shelemiah and Zephaniah the priest, the son of Maaseiah, to Jeremiah the prophet with the message, “Please pray to the LORD our God for us!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Now Jeremiah was free to come and go among the people, for they had not yet put him in prison.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Pharaoh’s army had left Egypt, and when the Chaldeans",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["37:5"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, the Babylonians; also in verses 8, 9, 13, and 14"]}],"caller":"+"},"who were besieging Jerusalem heard the report, they withdrew from Jerusalem."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Then the word of the LORD came to Jeremiah the prophet:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"“This is what the LORD, the God of Israel, says that you are to tell the king of Judah, who sent you to Me: Behold, Pharaoh’s army, which has marched out to help you, will go back to its own land of Egypt.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Then the Chaldeans will return and fight against this city. They will capture it and burn it down."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"This is what the LORD says: Do not deceive yourselves by saying, ‘The Chaldeans will go away for good,’ for they will not!",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Indeed, if you were to strike down the entire army of the Chaldeans that is fighting against you, and only wounded men remained in their tents, they would still get up and burn this city down.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jeremiah Imprisoned"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"When the Chaldean army withdrew from Jerusalem for fear of Pharaoh’s army,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Jeremiah started to leave Jerusalem to go to the land of Benjamin to claim his portion there",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["37:12"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["to divide from there"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"among the people.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"But when he reached the Gate of Benjamin, the captain of the guard, whose name was Irijah son of Shelemiah, the son of Hananiah, seized him and said, “You are deserting to the Chaldeans!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"“That is a lie,” Jeremiah replied. “I am not deserting to the Chaldeans!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["But Irijah would not listen to him; instead, he arrested Jeremiah and took him to the officials."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"The officials were angry with Jeremiah, and they beat him and placed him in jail in the house of Jonathan the scribe, for it had been made into a prison."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"So Jeremiah went into a cell in the dungeon and remained there a long time."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Later, King Zedekiah sent for Jeremiah and received him in his palace, where he asked him privately, “Is there a word from the LORD?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“There is,” Jeremiah replied. “You will be delivered into the hand of the king of Babylon.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Then Jeremiah asked King Zedekiah, “How have I sinned against you or your servants or these people, that you have put me in prison?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Where are your prophets who prophesied to you, claiming, ‘The king of Babylon will not come against you or this land’?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"But now please listen, O my lord the king. May my petition come before you. Do not send me back to the house of Jonathan the scribe, or I will die there.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"So King Zedekiah gave orders for Jeremiah to be placed in the courtyard of the guard and given a loaf of bread daily from the street of the bakers, until all the bread in the city was gone. So Jeremiah remained in the courtyard of the guard."]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"38"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jeremiah Cast into the Cistern"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Now Shephatiah son of Mattan, Gedaliah son of Pashhur, Jucal",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["38:1"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Jucal"]}," is a variant of ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Jehucal"]},"; see",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Jeremiah 37:3"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"son of Shelemiah, and Pashhur son of Malchijah heard that Jeremiah had been telling all the people:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"“This is what the LORD says: Whoever stays in this city will die by sword and famine and plague, but whoever surrenders to the Chaldeans",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["38:2"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, the Babylonians; also in verses 18, 19, and 23"]}],"caller":"+"},"will live; he will retain his life like a spoil of war, and he will live.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"This is what the LORD says: This city will surely be delivered into the hands of the army of the king of Babylon, and he will capture it.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Then the officials said to the king, “This man ought to die, for he is discouraging the warriors who remain in this city, as well as all the people, by speaking such words to them; this man is not seeking the well-being of these people, but their ruin.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"“Here he is,” replied King Zedekiah. “He is in your hands, since the king can do nothing to stop you.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"So they took Jeremiah and dropped him into the cistern of Malchiah, the king’s son, which was in the courtyard of the guard. They lowered Jeremiah with ropes into the cistern, which had no water but only mud, and Jeremiah sank down into the mud.",{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":[""]},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Now Ebed-melech the Cushite,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["38:7"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Probably from the upper Nile region"]}],"caller":"+"},"a court official",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["38:7"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["eunuch"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"in the royal palace, heard that Jeremiah had been put into the cistern. While the king was sitting at the Gate of Benjamin,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Ebed-melech went out from the king’s palace and said to the king,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"“My lord the king, these men have acted wickedly in all that they have done to Jeremiah the prophet. They have dropped him into the cistern, where he will starve to death, for there is no more bread in the city.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"So the king commanded Ebed-melech the Cushite, “Take thirty men from here with you and pull Jeremiah the prophet out of the cistern before he dies.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Then Ebed-melech took the men with him and went to the king’s palace, to a place below the storehouse. From there he took old rags and worn-out clothes and lowered them with ropes to Jeremiah in the cistern."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Ebed-melech the Cushite cried out to Jeremiah, “Put these worn-out rags and clothes under your arms to pad the ropes.” Jeremiah did so,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"and they pulled him up with the ropes and lifted him out of the cistern. And Jeremiah remained in the courtyard of the guard."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Then King Zedekiah sent for Jeremiah the prophet and received him at the third entrance to the house of the LORD. “I am going to ask you something,” said the king to Jeremiah. “Do not hide anything from me.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"“If I tell you,” Jeremiah replied, “you will surely put me to death. And even if I give you advice, you will not listen to me.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"But King Zedekiah swore secretly to Jeremiah, “As surely as the LORD lives, who has given us this life, I will not kill you, nor will I deliver you into the hands of these men who are seeking your life.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Then Jeremiah said to Zedekiah, “This is what the LORD God of Hosts, the God of Israel, says: ‘If you indeed surrender to the officers of the king of Babylon, then you will live, this city will not be burned down, and you and your household will survive.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"But if you do not surrender to the officers of the king of Babylon, then this city will be delivered into the hands of the Chaldeans. They will burn it down, and you yourself will not escape their grasp.’”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"But King Zedekiah said to Jeremiah, “I am afraid of the Jews who have deserted to the Chaldeans, for the Chaldeans may deliver me into their hands to abuse me.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"“They will not hand you over,” Jeremiah replied. “Obey the voice of the LORD in what I am telling you, that it may go well with you and you may live.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"But if you refuse to surrender, this is the word that the LORD has shown me:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"All the women who remain in the palace of the king of Judah will be brought out to the officials of the king of Babylon, and those women will say:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘They misled you and overcame you—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["those trusted friends of yours."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Your feet sank into the mire,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they deserted you.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"All your wives and children will be brought out to the Chaldeans. And you yourself will not escape their grasp, for you will be seized by the king of Babylon, and this city will be burned down.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Then Zedekiah warned Jeremiah, “Do not let anyone know about this conversation, or you will die.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"If the officials hear that I have spoken with you, and they come and demand of you, ‘Tell us what you said to the king and what he said to you; do not hide it from us, or we will kill you,’",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"then tell them, ‘I was presenting to the king my petition that he not return me to the house of Jonathan to die there.’”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"When all the officials came to Jeremiah and questioned him, he relayed to them the exact words the king had commanded him to say. So they said no more to him, for no one had overheard the conversation.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"And Jeremiah remained in the courtyard of the guard until the day Jerusalem was captured."]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"39"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Fall of Jerusalem"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(2 Kings 25:1–12; 2 Chronicles 36:15–21)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"In the ninth year of Zedekiah king of Judah, in the tenth month, Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon marched against Jerusalem with his entire army and laid siege to the city.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"And on the ninth day of the fourth month of Zedekiah’s eleventh year, the city was breached."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Then all the officials of the king of Babylon entered and sat in the Middle Gate: Nergal-sharezer of Samgar, Nebo-sarsekim",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["39:3"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Nergal-sharezer, Samgar-nebo, Sarsekim"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"the Rabsaris,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["39:3"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Rabsaris"]}," is the title of the chief eunuch in the Assyrian military; also in verse 13."]}],"caller":"+"},"Nergal-sharezer the Rabmag,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["39:3"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Rabmag"]}," is the title of the chief soothsayer or chief of princes in the Assyrian military; also in verse 13."]}],"caller":"+"},"and all the rest of the officials of the king of Babylon."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"When Zedekiah king of Judah and all the soldiers saw them, they fled. They left the city at night by way of the king’s garden, through the gate between the two walls, and they went out along the route to the Arabah.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["39:4"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["the Jordan Valley"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"But the army of the Chaldeans",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["39:5"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, the Babylonians; also in verse 8"]}],"caller":"+"},"pursued them and overtook Zedekiah in the plains of Jericho. They seized him and brought him up to Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon at Riblah in the land of Hamath, where he pronounced judgment on him."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"There at Riblah the king of Babylon slaughtered the sons of Zedekiah before his eyes, and he also killed all the nobles of Judah.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Then he put out Zedekiah’s eyes and bound him with bronze chains to take him to Babylon."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"The Chaldeans set fire to the palace of the king and to the houses of the people, and they broke down the walls of Jerusalem."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Then Nebuzaradan captain of the guard carried away to Babylon the remnant of the people who had remained in the city, along with the deserters who had defected to him.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"But Nebuzaradan left behind in the land of Judah some of the poor people who had no property, and at that time he gave them vineyards and fields."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jeremiah Delivered"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Now Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon had given orders about Jeremiah through Nebuzaradan captain of the guard, saying,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"“Take him, look after him, and do not let any harm come to him; do for him whatever he says.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"So Nebuzaradan captain of the guard, Nebushazban",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["39:13"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Nebushazban"]}," is possibly a variant of ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Nebo-sarsekim"]},"; see verse 3."]}],"caller":"+"},"the Rabsaris, Nergal-sharezer the Rabmag, and all the captains of the king of Babylon",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"had Jeremiah brought from the courtyard of the guard, and they turned him over to Gedaliah son of Ahikam, the son of Shaphan, to take him home. So Jeremiah remained among his own people."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"And while Jeremiah had been confined in the courtyard of the guard, the word of the LORD had come to him:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"“Go and tell Ebed-melech the Cushite that this is what the LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel, says: ‘I am about to fulfill My words against this city for harm and not for good, and on that day they will be fulfilled before your eyes.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"But I will deliver you on that day, declares the LORD, and you will not be delivered into the hands of the men whom you fear.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"For I will surely rescue you so that you do not fall by the sword. Because you have trusted in Me, you will escape with your life like a spoil of war, declares the LORD.’”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"40"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jeremiah Remains in Judah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"This is the word that came to Jeremiah from the LORD after Nebuzaradan captain of the guard had released him at Ramah, having found him bound in chains among all the captives of Jerusalem and Judah who were being exiled to Babylon."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"The captain of the guard found Jeremiah and said to him, “The LORD your God decreed this disaster on this place,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"and now the LORD has fulfilled it; He has done just as He said. Because you people have sinned against the LORD and have not obeyed His voice, this thing has happened to you.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"But now, behold, I am freeing you today from the chains that were on your wrists. If it pleases you to come with me to Babylon, then come, and I will take care of you. But if it seems wrong to you to come with me to Babylon, go no farther. Look, the whole land is before you. Wherever it seems good and right to you, go there.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"But before Jeremiah turned to go, Nebuzaradan added, “Return to Gedaliah son of Ahikam, the son of Shaphan, whom the king of Babylon has appointed over the cities of Judah, and stay with him among the people, or go anywhere else that seems right.” Then the captain of the guard gave him a ration and a gift and released him."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"So Jeremiah went to Gedaliah son of Ahikam at Mizpah and stayed with him among the people who were left in the land."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Gedaliah Governs in Judah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(2 Kings 25:22–24)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"When all the commanders and men of the armies in the field heard that the king of Babylon had appointed Gedaliah son of Ahikam over the land and that he had put him in charge of the men, women, and children who were the poorest of the land and had not been exiled to Babylon,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"they came to Gedaliah at Mizpah—Ishmael son of Nethaniah, Johanan and Jonathan the sons of Kareah, Seraiah son of Tanhumeth, the sons of Ephai the Netophathite, and Jezaniah",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["40:8"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Jezaniah"]}," is a variant of ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Jaazaniah"]},"; see",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["2 Kings 25:23"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"son of the Maacathite—they and their men."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Gedaliah son of Ahikam, the son of Shaphan, swore an oath to them and their men, assuring them, “Do not be afraid to serve the Chaldeans.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["40:9"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, the Babylonians; also in verse 10"]}],"caller":"+"},"Live in the land and serve the king of Babylon, and it will go well with you.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"As for me, I will stay in Mizpah to represent you before the Chaldeans who come to us. As for you, gather wine grapes, summer fruit, and oil, place them in your storage jars, and live in the cities you have taken.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"When all the Jews in Moab, Ammon, Edom, and all the other lands heard that the king of Babylon had left a remnant in Judah and had appointed Gedaliah son of Ahikam, the son of Shaphan, over them,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"they all returned from all the places to which they had been banished and came to the land of Judah, to Gedaliah at Mizpah. And they gathered an abundance of wine grapes and summer fruit."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Plot against Gedaliah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Meanwhile, Johanan son of Kareah and all the commanders of the armies in the field came to Gedaliah at Mizpah",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"and said to him, “Are you aware that Baalis king of the Ammonites has sent Ishmael son of Nethaniah to take your life?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["But Gedaliah son of Ahikam did not believe them."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Then Johanan son of Kareah spoke privately to Gedaliah at Mizpah. “Let me go and kill Ishmael son of Nethaniah,” he said. “No one will know it. Why should he take your life and scatter all the people of Judah who have gathered to you, so that the remnant of Judah would perish?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"But Gedaliah son of Ahikam said to Johanan son of Kareah, “Do not do such a thing! What you are saying about Ishmael is a lie.”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"41"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Murder of Gedaliah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(2 Kings 25:25–26)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"In the seventh month, Ishmael son of Nethaniah, the son of Elishama, who was a member of the royal family and one of the king’s chief officers, came with ten men to Gedaliah son of Ahikam at Mizpah, and they ate a meal together there.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"Then Ishmael son of Nethaniah and the ten men who were with him got up and struck down Gedaliah son of Ahikam, the son of Shaphan, with the sword, killing the one whom the king of Babylon had appointed to govern the land.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Ishmael also killed all the Jews who were with Gedaliah at Mizpah, as well as the Chaldean",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["41:3"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Babylonian"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"soldiers who were there."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"On the second day after the murder of Gedaliah, when no one yet knew about it,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"eighty men who had shaved off their beards, torn their garments, and cut themselves came from Shechem, Shiloh, and Samaria, carrying grain offerings and frankincense for the house of the LORD.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"And Ishmael son of Nethaniah went out from Mizpah to meet them, weeping as he went."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["When Ishmael encountered the men, he said, “Come to Gedaliah son of Ahikam.”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"And when they came into the city, Ishmael son of Nethaniah and the men with him slaughtered them and threw them into a cistern."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"But ten of the men among them said to Ishmael, “Do not kill us, for we have hidden treasure in the field—wheat, barley, oil, and honey!” So he refrained from killing them with the others."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Now the cistern into which Ishmael had thrown all the bodies of the men he had struck down along with Gedaliah was a large one that King Asa had made for fear of Baasha king of Israel. Ishmael son of Nethaniah filled it with the slain."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Then Ishmael took captive all the remnant of the people of Mizpah—the daughters of the king along with all the others who remained in Mizpah—over whom Nebuzaradan captain of the guard had appointed Gedaliah son of Ahikam. Ishmael son of Nethaniah took them captive and set off to cross over to the Ammonites."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Johanan Rescues the Captives"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"When Johanan son of Kareah and all the commanders of the armies with him heard of all the crimes that Ishmael son of Nethaniah had committed,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"they took all their men and went to fight Ishmael son of Nethaniah. And they found him near the great pool in Gibeon."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"When all the people with Ishmael saw Johanan son of Kareah and all the commanders of the army with him, they rejoiced,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"and all the people whom Ishmael had taken captive at Mizpah turned and went over to Johanan son of Kareah.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"But Ishmael son of Nethaniah and eight of his men escaped from Johanan and went to the Ammonites."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Then Johanan son of Kareah and all the commanders of the armies with him took the whole remnant of the people from Mizpah whom he had recovered from Ishmael son of Nethaniah after Ishmael had killed Gedaliah son of Ahikam: the soldiers, women, children, and court officials",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["41:16"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["eunuchs"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"he had brought back from Gibeon.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"And they went and stayed in Geruth Chimham, near Bethlehem, in order to proceed into Egypt",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"to escape the Chaldeans.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["41:18"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, the Babylonians"]}],"caller":"+"},"For they were afraid of the Chaldeans because Ishmael son of Nethaniah had struck down Gedaliah son of Ahikam, whom the king of Babylon had appointed over the land."]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"42"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["A Warning against Going to Egypt"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Then all the commanders of the forces, along with Johanan son of Kareah, Jezaniah",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["42:1"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew; LXX ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Azariah"]},"; see",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Jeremiah 43:2"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"son of Hoshaiah, and all the people from the least to the greatest, approached",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"Jeremiah the prophet and said, “May our petition come before you; pray to the LORD your God on behalf of this entire remnant. For few of us remain of the many, as you can see with your own eyes.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Pray that the LORD your God will tell us the way we should walk and the thing we should do.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"“I have heard you,” replied Jeremiah the prophet. “I will surely pray to the LORD your God as you request, and I will tell you everything that the LORD answers. I will not withhold a word from you.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Then they said to Jeremiah, “May the LORD be a true and faithful witness against us if we do not act upon every word that the LORD your God sends you to tell us.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Whether it is pleasant or unpleasant, we will obey the voice of the LORD our God to whom we are sending you, so that it may go well with us when we obey the voice of the LORD our God!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"After ten days the word of the LORD came to Jeremiah,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"and he summoned Johanan son of Kareah, all the commanders of the forces who were with him, and all the people from the least to the greatest."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Jeremiah told them, “Thus says the LORD, the God of Israel, to whom you sent me to present your petition:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"‘If you will indeed stay in this land, then I will build you up and not tear you down; I will plant you and not uproot you, for I will relent of the disaster I have brought upon you."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Do not be afraid of the king of Babylon, whom you now fear; do not be afraid of him, declares the LORD, for I am with you to save you and deliver you from him.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"And I will show you compassion, and he will have compassion on you and restore you to your own land.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"But if you say, ‘We will not stay in this land,’ and you thus disobey the voice of the LORD your God,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"and if you say, ‘No, but we will go to the land of Egypt and live there, where we will not see war or hear the sound of the ram’s horn or hunger for bread,’",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"then hear the word of the LORD, O remnant of Judah! This is what the LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel, says: ‘If you are determined to go to Egypt and reside there,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"then the sword you fear will overtake you there, and the famine you dread will follow on your heels into Egypt, and you will die there.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"So all who resolve to go to Egypt to reside there will die by sword and famine and plague. Not one of them will survive or escape the disaster I will bring upon them.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"For this is what the LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel, says: ‘Just as My anger and wrath were poured out on the residents of Jerusalem, so will My wrath be poured out on you if you go to Egypt. You will become an object of cursing and horror, of vilification and disgrace, and you will never see this place again.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"The LORD has told you, O remnant of Judah, ‘Do not go to Egypt.’ Know for sure that I have warned you today!",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"For you have deceived yourselves by sending me to the LORD your God, saying, ‘Pray to the LORD our God on our behalf, and as for all that the LORD our God says, tell it to us and we will do it.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"For I have told you today, but you have not obeyed the voice of the LORD your God in all He has sent me to tell you.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Now therefore, know for sure that by sword and famine and plague you will die in the place where you desire to go to reside.”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"43"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jeremiah Taken to Egypt"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"When Jeremiah had finished telling all the people all the words of the LORD their God—everything that the LORD had sent him to say—",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"Azariah son of Hoshaiah, Johanan son of Kareah, and all the arrogant men said to Jeremiah, “You are lying! The LORD our God has not sent you to say, ‘You must not go to Egypt to reside there.’",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Rather, Baruch son of Neriah is inciting you against us to deliver us into the hands of the Chaldeans,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["43:3"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, the Babylonians"]}],"caller":"+"},"so that they may put us to death or exile us to Babylon!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"So Johanan son of Kareah and all the commanders of the forces disobeyed the command of the LORD to stay in the land of Judah.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Instead, Johanan son of Kareah and all the commanders of the forces took the whole remnant of Judah, those who had returned to the land of Judah from all the nations to which they had been scattered,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"the men, the women, the children, the king’s daughters, and everyone whom Nebuzaradan captain of the guard had allowed to remain with Gedaliah son of Ahikam, the son of Shaphan, as well as Jeremiah the prophet and Baruch son of Neriah."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"So they entered the land of Egypt because they did not obey the voice of the LORD, and they went as far as Tahpanhes."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Then the word of the LORD came to Jeremiah at Tahpanhes:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"“In the sight of the Jews, pick up some large stones and bury them in the clay of the brick pavement at the entrance to Pharaoh’s palace at Tahpanhes."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Then tell them that this is what the LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel, says: ‘I will send for My servant Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, and I will set his throne over these stones that I have embedded, and he will spread his royal pavilion over them.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"He will come and strike down the land of Egypt, bringing death to those destined for death, captivity to those destined for captivity, and the sword to those destined for the sword."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"I will kindle a fire in the temples of the gods of Egypt, and Nebuchadnezzar will burn those temples and take their gods as captives.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["43:12"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["and he will burn them and take them captive"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"So he will wrap himself with the land of Egypt as a shepherd wraps himself in his garment, and he will depart from there unscathed.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"He will demolish the sacred pillars of the temple of the sun in the land of Egypt,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["43:13"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["LXX ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["He will demolish the pillars of Heliopolis in On"]}," or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["He will demolish the pillars of Heliopolis in Egypt"]},"; Hebrew ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["He will demolish the pillars of Beth-shemesh in the land of Egypt"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"and he will burn down the temples of the gods of Egypt.’”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"44"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Judgment on the Jews in Egypt"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"This is the word that came to Jeremiah concerning all the Jews living in the land of Egypt",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["44:1"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Lower Egypt"]}," or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["northern Egypt"]},"; also in verse 15"]}],"caller":"+"},"—in Migdol, Tahpanhes, and Memphis",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["44:1"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["LXX; Hebrew ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Noph"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"—and in the land of Pathros:",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["44:1"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Upper Egypt"]}," or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["southern Egypt"]},"; also in verse 15"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"“This is what the LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel, says: You have seen all the disaster that I brought against Jerusalem and all the cities of Judah; and behold, they lie today in ruins and desolation",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"because of the evil they have done."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They provoked Me to anger by continuing to burn incense and to serve other gods that neither they nor you nor your fathers ever knew.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Yet I sent you all My servants the prophets again and again,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["44:4"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["the prophets, rising up early and sending (them),"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"saying: ‘Do not do this detestable thing that I hate.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"But they did not listen or incline their ears; they did not turn from their wickedness or stop burning incense to other gods.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Therefore My wrath and anger poured out and burned in the cities of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem, so that they have become the desolate ruin they are today."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"So now, this is what the LORD God of Hosts, the God of Israel, says: Why are you doing such great harm to yourselves by cutting off from Judah man and woman, child and infant, leaving yourselves without a remnant?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Why are you provoking Me to anger by the work of your hands by burning incense to other gods in the land of Egypt, where you have gone to reside?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["As a result, you will be cut off and will become an object of cursing and reproach among all the nations of the earth.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Have you forgotten the wickedness of your fathers and of the kings of Judah and their wives, as well as the wickedness that you and your wives committed in the land of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"To this day they have not humbled themselves or shown reverence, nor have they followed My instruction or the statutes that I set before you and your fathers."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Therefore this is what the LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel, says: I will set My face to bring disaster and to cut off all Judah.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"And I will take away the remnant of Judah who have resolved to go to the land of Egypt to reside there; they will meet their end. They will all fall by the sword or be consumed by famine. From the least to the greatest, they will die by sword or famine; and they will become an object of cursing and horror, of vilification and reproach."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"I will punish those who live in the land of Egypt, just as I punished Jerusalem, by sword and famine and plague,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"so that none of the remnant of Judah who have gone to reside in Egypt will escape or survive to return to the land of Judah, where they long to return and live; for none will return except a few fugitives.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Stubbornness of the People"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Then all the men who knew that their wives were burning incense to other gods, and all the women standing by—a great assembly—along with all the people living in the land of Egypt and in Pathros,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["44:15"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, in Lower and Upper Egypt; possibly ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["in the land of Egypt at Pathros"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"said to Jeremiah,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"“As for the word you have spoken to us in the name of the LORD, we will not listen to you!",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Instead, we will do everything we vowed to do: We will burn incense to the Queen of Heaven and offer drink offerings to her, just as we, our fathers, our kings, and our officials did in the cities of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["At that time we had plenty of food and good things, and we saw no disaster.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"But from the time we stopped burning incense to the Queen of Heaven and pouring out drink offerings to her, we have lacked everything and have been perishing by sword and famine.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"“Moreover,” said the women, “when we burned incense to the Queen of Heaven and poured out drink offerings to her, was it without our husbands’ knowledge that we made sacrificial cakes in her image and poured out drink offerings to her?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Calamity for the Jews"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Then Jeremiah said to all the people, both men and women, who were answering him,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"“As for the incense you burned in the cities of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem—you, your fathers, your kings, your officials, and the people of the land—did the LORD not remember and bring this to mind?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"So the LORD could no longer endure the evil deeds and detestable acts you committed, and your land became a desolation, a horror, and an object of cursing, without inhabitant, as it is this day.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Because you burned incense and sinned against the LORD and did not obey the voice of the LORD or walk in His instruction, His statutes, and His testimonies, this disaster has befallen you, as you see today.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Then Jeremiah said to all the people, including all the women, “Hear the word of the LORD, all those of Judah who are in the land of Egypt.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"This is what the LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel, says: As for you and your wives, you have spoken with your mouths and fulfilled with your hands your words: ‘We will surely perform our vows that we have made to burn incense to the Queen of Heaven and to pour out drink offerings to her.’ Go ahead, then, do what you have promised! Keep your vows!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"Nevertheless, hear the word of the LORD, all you people of Judah living in Egypt: Behold, I have sworn by My great name, says the LORD, that never again will any man of Judah living in the land of Egypt invoke My name or say, ‘As surely as the Lord GOD lives.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"I am watching over them for harm and not for good, and every man of Judah who is in the land of Egypt will meet his end by sword or famine, until they are finished off."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"Those who escape the sword will return from Egypt to Judah, few in number, and the whole remnant of Judah who went to dwell in the land of Egypt will know whose word will stand, Mine or theirs!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"This will be a sign to you that I will punish you in this place, declares the LORD, so that you may know that My threats of harm against you will surely stand.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"This is what the LORD says: Behold, I will deliver Pharaoh Hophra king of Egypt into the hands of his enemies who seek his life, just as I delivered Zedekiah king of Judah into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, the enemy who was seeking his life.”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"45"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jeremiah’s Message to Baruch"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"This is the word that Jeremiah the prophet spoke to Baruch son of Neriah when he wrote these words on a scroll at the dictation of Jeremiah in the fourth year of Jehoiakim son of Josiah, king of Judah:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"“This is what the LORD, the God of Israel, says to you, Baruch:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"You have said, ‘Woe is me because the LORD has added sorrow to my pain! I am worn out with groaning and have found no rest.’”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Thus Jeremiah was to say to Baruch:",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["45:4"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["Thus you shall say to him:"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"“This is what the LORD says: Throughout the land I will demolish what I have built and uproot what I have planted.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"But as for you, do you seek great things for yourself? Stop seeking! For I will bring disaster on every living creature, declares the LORD, but wherever you go, I will grant your life as a spoil of war.”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"46"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Judgment on Egypt"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"This is the word of the LORD about the nations—the word that came to Jeremiah the prophet",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"concerning Egypt and the army of Pharaoh Neco king of Egypt, which was defeated at Carchemish on the Euphrates River by Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon in the fourth year of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah king of Judah:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"“Deploy your shields, small and large;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["advance for battle!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Harness the horses; mount the steeds;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["take your positions with helmets on!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Polish your spears;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["put on armor!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Why am I seeing this?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They are terrified,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they are retreating;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["their warriors are defeated,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they flee in haste without looking back;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["terror is on every side!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"“The swift cannot flee,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the warrior cannot escape!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["In the north by the River Euphrates"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they stumble and fall."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Who is this, rising like the Nile,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like rivers whose waters churn?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Egypt rises like the Nile,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and its waters churn like rivers,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["boasting, ‘I will rise and cover the earth;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will destroy the cities and their people.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Advance, O horses! Race furiously, O chariots!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Let the warriors come forth—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Cush",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["46:9"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, the upper Nile region"]}],"caller":"+"},"and Put carrying their shields,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["men of Lydia drawing the bow."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"For that day belongs to the Lord GOD of Hosts,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a day of vengeance against His foes."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The sword will devour until it is satisfied,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["until it is quenched with their blood."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For the Lord GOD of Hosts will hold a sacrifice"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in the land of the north by the River Euphrates."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Go up to Gilead for balm,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["O Virgin Daughter of Egypt!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["In vain you try many remedies,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but for you there is no healing."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"The nations have heard of your shame,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and your outcry fills the earth,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["because warrior stumbles over warrior"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and both of them have fallen together.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"This is the word that the LORD spoke to Jeremiah the prophet about the coming of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon to strike the land of Egypt:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"“Announce it in Egypt, and proclaim it in Migdol;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["proclaim it in Memphis",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["46:14"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["LXX; Hebrew ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Noph"]},"; also in verse 19"]}],"caller":"+"},"and Tahpanhes:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘Take your positions and prepare yourself,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the sword devours those around you.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Why have your warriors been laid low?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They cannot stand, for the LORD has thrust them down."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"They continue to stumble;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["indeed, they have fallen over one another."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They say, ‘Get up! Let us return to our people"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and to the land of our birth,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["away from the sword of the oppressor.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"There they will cry out:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘Pharaoh king of Egypt was all noise;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["he has let the appointed time pass him by.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"As surely as I live, declares the King,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["whose name is the LORD of Hosts,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["there will come one who is like Tabor among the mountains"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and like Carmel by the sea."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Pack your bags for exile,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["O daughter dwelling in Egypt!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For Memphis will be laid waste,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["destroyed and uninhabited."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Egypt is a beautiful heifer,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but a gadfly from the north is coming against her."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Even the mercenaries among her"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["are like fattened calves."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They too will turn back;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["together they will flee, they will not stand their ground,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for the day of calamity is coming upon them—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the time of their punishment."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Egypt will hiss like a fleeing serpent,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["46:22"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["nachash"]},"; translated in most cases as ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["snake"]},""]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for the enemy will advance in force;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["with axes they will come against her"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like woodsmen cutting down trees."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"They will chop down her forest, declares the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["dense though it may be,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for they are more numerous than locusts;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they cannot be counted."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"The Daughter of Egypt will be put to shame;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["she will be delivered into the hands of the people of the north.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"The LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel, says: “Behold, I am about to punish Amon god of Thebes,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["46:25"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Amon of No"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"along with Pharaoh, Egypt with her gods and kings, and those who trust in Pharaoh.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"I will deliver them into the hands of those who seek their lives—of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon and his officers. But after this, Egypt will be inhabited as in days of old, declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"But you, O Jacob My servant, do not be afraid,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and do not be dismayed, O Israel."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For I will surely save you out of a distant place,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["your descendants from the land of their captivity!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Jacob will return to quiet and ease,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with no one to make him afraid."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"And you, My servant Jacob, do not be afraid,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["declares the LORD, for I am with you."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Though I will completely destroy all the nations to which I have banished you,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will not completely destroy you."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Yet I will discipline you justly,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will by no means leave you unpunished.”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"47"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Judgment on the Philistines"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Zephaniah 2:4–7)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"This is the word of the LORD that came to Jeremiah the prophet about the Philistines before Pharaoh struck down Gaza.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"This is what the LORD says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“See how the waters are rising from the north"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and becoming an overflowing torrent."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They will overflow the land and its fullness,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the cities and their inhabitants."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The people will cry out,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and all who dwell in the land will wail"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"at the sound of the galloping hooves of stallions,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the rumbling of chariots,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the clatter of their wheels."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The fathers will not turn back for their sons;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["their hands will hang limp."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"For the day has come"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to destroy all the Philistines,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["to cut off from Tyre and Sidon"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["every remaining ally."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Indeed, the LORD is about to destroy the Philistines,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the remnant from the coasts of Caphtor.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["47:4"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, Crete"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"The people of Gaza will shave their heads in mourning;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Ashkelon will be silenced."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["O remnant of their valley,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["47:5"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, the Mediterranean coast or plain"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["how long will you gash yourself?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"‘Alas, O sword of the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["how long until you rest?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Return to your sheath;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["cease and be still!’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"How can it rest"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["when the LORD has commanded it?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["He has appointed it against Ashkelon"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the shore of its coastland.”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"48"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Judgment on Moab"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Isaiah 15:1–9)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Concerning Moab, this is what the LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel, says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Woe to Nebo,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for it will be devastated."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Kiriathaim will be captured and disgraced;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the fortress will be shattered and dismantled."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"There is no longer praise for Moab;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in Heshbon",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["48:2"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["The Hebrew for ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Heshbon"]}," sounds like the Hebrew for ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["plot"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"they devise evil against her:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘Come, let us cut her off from nationhood.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["You too, O people of Madmen,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["48:2"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["The name of the Moabite town ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Madmen"]}," sounds like the Hebrew for ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["silenced"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"will be silenced;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the sword will pursue you."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"A voice cries out from Horonaim:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘Devastation and great destruction!’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Moab will be shattered;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["her little ones will cry out.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["48:4"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew; LXX ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["her cries are heard as far away as Zoar"]},""]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"For on the ascent to Luhith"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they weep bitterly as they go,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and on the descent to Horonaim"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["cries of distress resound"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["over the destruction:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"‘Flee! Run for your lives!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Become like a juniper in the desert.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["48:6"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["like a wild donkey"]}," or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["like Aroer"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Because you trust in your works and treasures,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["you too will be captured,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and Chemosh will go into exile"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with his priests and officials."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"The destroyer will move against every city,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and not one town will escape."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The valley will also be ruined,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the high plain will be destroyed,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["as the LORD has said."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Put salt on Moab,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for she will be laid waste;",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["48:9"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Give wings to Moab, for she would fly away"]},""]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["her cities will become desolate,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with no one to dwell in them."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Cursed is the one who is remiss"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in doing the work of the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and cursed is he who withholds"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["his sword from bloodshed."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Moab has been at ease from youth,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["settled like wine on its dregs;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["he has not been poured from vessel to vessel"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["or gone into exile."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["So his flavor has remained the same,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and his aroma is unchanged."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Therefore behold, the days are coming,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["declares the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["when I will send to him wanderers,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["who will pour him out."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They will empty his vessels"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and shatter his jars."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Then Moab will be ashamed of Chemosh,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["just as the house of Israel was ashamed"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["when they trusted in Bethel."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"How can you say, ‘We are warriors,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["mighty men ready for battle’?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Moab has been destroyed"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and its towns have been invaded;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["the best of its young men"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["have gone down in the slaughter,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["declares the King,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["whose name is the LORD of Hosts."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Moab’s calamity is at hand,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and his affliction is rushing swiftly."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Mourn for him, all you who surround him,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["everyone who knows his name;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["tell how the mighty scepter is shattered—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the glorious staff!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Come down from your glory; sit on parched ground,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["O daughter dwelling in Dibon,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for the destroyer of Moab has come against you;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["he has destroyed your fortresses."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Stand by the road and watch,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["O dweller of Aroer!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Ask the man fleeing or the woman escaping,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘What has happened?’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Moab is put to shame, for it has been shattered."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Wail and cry out!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Declare by the Arnon"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that Moab is destroyed."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Judgment has come upon the high plain—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["upon Holon, Jahzah,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["48:21"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Jahzah"]}," is a variant of ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Jahaz"]},"; see verse 34."]}],"caller":"+"},"and Mephaath,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"upon Dibon, Nebo, and Beth-diblathaim,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"upon Kiriathaim, Beth-gamul, and Beth-meon,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"upon Kerioth, Bozrah, and all the towns of Moab,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["those far and near."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"The horn of Moab has been cut off,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and his arm is broken,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"“Make him drunk,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because he has magnified himself against the LORD;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["so Moab will wallow in his own vomit,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and he will also become a laughingstock."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"Was not Israel your object of ridicule?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Was he ever found among thieves?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For whenever you speak of him"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["you shake your head."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"Abandon the towns and settle among the rocks,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["O dwellers of Moab!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Be like a dove"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that nests at the mouth of a cave."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"We have heard of Moab’s pomposity,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["his exceeding pride and conceit,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["his proud arrogance and haughtiness of heart."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"I know his insolence,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“but it is futile."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["His boasting is as empty as his deeds."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"Therefore I will wail for Moab;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will cry out for all of Moab;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will moan for the men of Kir-heres.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["48:31"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Kir-heres"]}," is a variant of ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Kir-hareseth"]},"; also in verse 36; see",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Isaiah 16:7"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"I will weep for you, O vine of Sibmah,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["more than I weep for Jazer."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Your tendrils have extended to the sea;",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["48:32"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Probably the Dead Sea"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they reach even to Jazer.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["48:32"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Two Hebrew manuscripts and LXX; most Hebrew manuscripts ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["to the Sea of Jazer"]},""]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The destroyer has descended"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["on your summer fruit and grape harvest."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"Joy and gladness are removed from the orchard"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and from the fields of Moab."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I have stopped the flow of wine from the presses;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["no one treads them with shouts of joy;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["their shouts are not for joy."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"There is a cry from Heshbon to Elealeh;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they raise their voices to Jahaz,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["from Zoar to Horonaim and Eglath-shelishiyah;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for even the waters of Nimrim have dried up."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"In Moab, declares the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will bring an end"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["to those who make offerings on the high places"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and burn incense to their gods."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"Therefore My heart laments like a flute for Moab;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["it laments like a flute for the men of Kir-heres,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because the wealth they acquired has perished."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"For every head is shaved"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and every beard is clipped;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["on every hand is a gash,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and around every waist is sackcloth."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"On all the rooftops of Moab"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and in the public squares,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["everyone is mourning;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for I have shattered Moab like an unwanted jar,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"“How shattered it is! How they wail!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["How Moab has turned his back in shame!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Moab has become an object of ridicule and horror"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to all those around him.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40"},"For this is what the LORD says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Behold, an eagle swoops down"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and spreads his wings against Moab."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41"},"Kirioth has been taken,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the strongholds seized."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["In that day the heart of Moab’s warriors"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["will be like the heart of a woman in labor."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42"},"Moab will be destroyed as a nation"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because he vaunted himself against the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43"},"Terror and pit and snare await you, O dweller of Moab,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44"},"“Whoever flees the panic"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["will fall into the pit,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and whoever climbs from the pit"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["will be caught in the snare."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For I will bring upon Moab"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the year of their punishment,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45"},"“Those who flee will stand helpless in Heshbon’s shadow,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because fire has gone forth from Heshbon"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and a flame from within Sihon."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["It devours the foreheads of Moab"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the skulls of the sons of tumult."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46"},"Woe to you, O Moab!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The people of Chemosh have perished;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for your sons have been taken into exile"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and your daughters have gone into captivity."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47"},"Yet in the latter days I will restore Moab from captivity,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["48:47"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["restore the fortunes of Moab"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Here ends the judgment on Moab."]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"49"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Judgment on the Ammonites"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Concerning the Ammonites, this is what the LORD says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Has Israel no sons?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Is he without heir?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Why then has Milcom",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["49:1"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["their king"]},"; ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Milcom"]}," is a variant of ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Molech"]},"; also in verse 3; see",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Leviticus 18:21"]},"and",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["1 Kings 11:7"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"taken possession of Gad?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Why have his people settled in their cities?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"Therefore, behold, the days are coming,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["declares the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["when I will sound the battle cry"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["against Rabbah of the Ammonites."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["It will become a heap of ruins,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and its villages will be burned."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Then Israel will drive out their dispossessors,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["says the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Wail, O Heshbon, for Ai has been destroyed;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["cry out, O daughters of Rabbah!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Put on sackcloth and mourn;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["run back and forth within your walls,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for Milcom will go into exile"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["together with his priests and officials."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Why do you boast of your valleys—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["your valleys so fruitful,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["49:4"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["your valleys flowing"]},""]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["O faithless daughter?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["You trust in your riches and say,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘Who can come against me?’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Behold, I am about to bring terror upon you,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["declares the Lord GOD of Hosts,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from all those around you."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["You will each be driven headlong,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with no one to regather the fugitives."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Yet afterward I will restore the Ammonites from captivity,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["49:6"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["restore the fortunes of the Ammonites"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Judgment on Edom"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Obadiah 1:1–14)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Concerning Edom, this is what the LORD of Hosts says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Is there no longer wisdom in Teman?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Has counsel perished from the prudent?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Has their wisdom decayed?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Turn and run!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Lie low, O dwellers of Dedan,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for I will bring disaster on Esau"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["at the time I punish him."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"If grape gatherers came to you,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["would they not leave some gleanings?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Were thieves to come in the night,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["would they not steal only what they wanted?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"But I will strip Esau bare;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will uncover his hiding places,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and he will be unable to conceal himself."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["His descendants will be destroyed"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["along with his relatives and neighbors,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and he will be no more."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Abandon your orphans; I will preserve their lives."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Let your widows trust in Me.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"For this is what the LORD says: “If those who do not deserve to drink the cup must drink it, can you possibly remain unpunished? You will not go unpunished, for you must drink it too.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"For by Myself I have sworn, declares the LORD, that Bozrah will become a desolation, a disgrace, a ruin, and a curse, and all her cities will be in ruins forever.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"I have heard a message from the LORD;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["an envoy has been sent to the nations:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Assemble yourselves to march against her!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Rise up for battle!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"“For behold, I will make you small among nations,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["despised among men."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"The terror you cause"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the pride of your heart"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["have deceived you,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["O dwellers in the clefts of the rocks,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["49:16"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["of Sela"]},""]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["O occupiers of the mountain summit."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Though you elevate your nest like the eagle,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["even from there I will bring you down,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"“Edom will become an object of horror."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["All who pass by will be appalled"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will scoff at all her wounds."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"As Sodom and Gomorrah were overthrown"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["along with their neighbors,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["says the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“no one will dwell there;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["no man will abide there."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Behold, one will come up like a lion"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from the thickets of the Jordan to the watered pasture."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For in an instant I will chase Edom from her land."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Who is the chosen one I will appoint for this?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For who is like Me, and who can challenge Me?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["What shepherd can stand against Me?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Therefore hear the plans"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that the LORD has drawn up against Edom"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and the strategies He has devised"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["against the people of Teman:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Surely the little ones of the flock will be dragged away;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["certainly their pasture will be made desolate because of them.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["49:20"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["their pasture will be appalled at their fate"]},""]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"At the sound of their fall the earth will quake;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["their cry will resound to the Red Sea.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["49:21"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["the Sea of Reeds"]},""]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Look! An eagle will soar and swoop down,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["spreading its wings over Bozrah."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["In that day the hearts of Edom’s mighty men"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["will be like the heart of a woman in labor."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Judgment on Damascus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Isaiah 17:1–14)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Concerning Damascus:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Hamath and Arpad are put to shame,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for they have heard a bad report;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["they are agitated like the sea;",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["49:23"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["on the sea"]}," or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["by the sea"]},""]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["their anxiety cannot be calmed."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Damascus has become feeble;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["she has turned to flee."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Panic has gripped her;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["anguish and pain have seized her"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like a woman in labor."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"How is the city of praise not forsaken,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the town that brings Me joy?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"For her young men will fall in the streets,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and all her warriors will be silenced in that day,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD of Hosts."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"“I will set fire to the walls of Damascus;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["it will consume the fortresses of Ben-hadad.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Judgment on Kedar and Hazor"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"Concerning Kedar and the kingdoms of Hazor, which Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon defeated, this is what the LORD says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Rise up, advance against Kedar,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and destroy the people of the east!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"They will take their tents and flocks,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["their tent curtains and all their goods."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They will take their camels for themselves."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They will shout to them: ‘Terror is on every side!’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"Run! Escape quickly!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Lie low, O residents of Hazor,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“for Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["has drawn up a plan against you;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["he has devised a strategy against you."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"Rise up, advance against a nation at ease,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["one that dwells securely,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“They have no gates or bars;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they live alone."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"Their camels will become plunder,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and their large herds will be spoil."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will scatter to the wind in every direction"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["those who shave their temples;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will bring calamity on them"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from all sides,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"“Hazor will become a haunt for jackals,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["49:33"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["serpents"]}," or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["dragons"]},""]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a desolation forever."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["No one will dwell there;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["no man will abide there.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Judgment on Elam"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"This is the word of the LORD that came to Jeremiah the prophet concerning Elam at the beginning of the reign of Zedekiah king of Judah.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"This is what the LORD of Hosts says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Behold, I will shatter Elam’s bow,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the mainstay of their might."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"I will bring the four winds against Elam"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from the four corners of the heavens,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and I will scatter them"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to all these winds."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["There will not be a nation"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to which Elam’s exiles will not go."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"So I will shatter Elam before their foes,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["before those who seek their lives."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will bring disaster upon them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["even My fierce anger,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“I will send out the sword after them"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["until I finish them off."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"I will set My throne in Elam,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and destroy its king and officials,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"“Yet in the last days,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will restore Elam from captivity,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["49:39"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["restore the fortunes of Elam"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"50"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["A Prophecy against Babylon"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"This is the word that the LORD spoke through Jeremiah the prophet concerning Babylon and the land of the Chaldeans:",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["50:1"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, the Babylonians; also in verses 8, 25, 35, and 45"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"“Announce and declare to the nations;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["lift up a banner and proclaim it;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["hold nothing back when you say,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘Babylon is captured;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Bel is put to shame;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Marduk is shattered,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["her images are disgraced,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["her idols are broken in pieces.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"For a nation from the north will come against her;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["it will make her land a desolation."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["No one will live in it;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["both man and beast will flee.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Hope for Israel and Judah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"“In those days and at that time,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["declares the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["the children of Israel and the children of Judah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["will come together, weeping as they come,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will seek the LORD their God."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"They will ask the way to Zion"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and turn their faces toward it."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They will come and join themselves to the LORD"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in an everlasting covenant"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that will never be forgotten."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"My people are lost sheep;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["their shepherds have led them astray,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["causing them to roam the mountains."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They have wandered from mountain to hill;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they have forgotten their resting place."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"All who found them devoured them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and their enemies said,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘We are not guilty,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for they have sinned against the LORD, their true pasture,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the LORD, the hope of their fathers.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Flee from the midst of Babylon;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["depart from the 