a","marker":"q2","content":["and stretched out the heavens by His understanding."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"When He thunders,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the waters in the heavens roar;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["He causes the clouds to rise"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from the ends of the earth."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["He generates the lightning with the rain"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and brings forth the wind from His storehouses."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Every man is senseless and devoid of knowledge;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["every goldsmith is put to shame by his idols."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For his molten images are a fraud,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and there is no breath in them."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"They are worthless, a work to be mocked."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["In the time of their punishment they will perish."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"The Portion of Jacob is not like these,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for He is the Maker of all things,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and of the tribe of His inheritance—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the LORD of Hosts is His name."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Babylon’s Punishment"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"“You are My war club,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["My weapon for battle."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["With you I shatter nations;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with you I bring kingdoms to ruin."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"With you I shatter the horse and rider;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with you I shatter the chariot and driver."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"With you I shatter man and woman;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with you I shatter the old man and the youth;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with you I shatter the young man and the maiden."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"With you I shatter the shepherd and his flock;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with you I shatter the farmer and his oxen;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with you I shatter the governors and officials."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Before your very eyes I will repay"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Babylon and all the dwellers of Chaldea",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["51:24"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, Babylonia; also in verse 35"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for all the evil they have done in Zion,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"“Behold, I am against you,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["O destroying mountain,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["you who devastate the whole earth,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will stretch out My hand against you;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will roll you over the cliffs"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and turn you into a charred mountain."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"No one shall retrieve from you a cornerstone"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["or a foundation stone,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because you will become desolate forever,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"“Raise a banner in the land!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Blow the ram’s horn among the nations!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Prepare the nations against her."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Summon the kingdoms against her—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Ararat, Minni, and Ashkenaz."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Appoint a captain against her;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["bring up horses like swarming locusts."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"Prepare the nations for battle against her—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the kings of the Medes,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["their governors and all their officials,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and all the lands they rule."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"The earth quakes and writhes"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because the LORD’s intentions against Babylon stand:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["to make the land of Babylon a desolation,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["without inhabitant."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"The warriors of Babylon have stopped fighting;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they sit in their strongholds."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Their strength is exhausted;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they have become like women."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Babylon’s homes have been set ablaze,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the bars of her gates are broken."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"One courier races to meet another,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and messenger follows messenger,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["to announce to the king of Babylon"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that his city has been captured from end to end."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"The fords have been seized,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the marshes set on fire,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the soldiers are terrified.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"For this is what the LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel, says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“The Daughter of Babylon is like a threshing floor"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["at the time it is trampled."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["In just a little while"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["her harvest time will come.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"“Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon has devoured me;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["he has crushed me."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["He has set me aside like an empty vessel;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["he has swallowed me like a monster;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["he filled his belly with my delicacies"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and vomited me out.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["51:34"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["expelled me"]},""]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"May the violence done to me"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and to my flesh"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["be upon Babylon,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["says the dweller of Zion."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“May my blood be on the dwellers of Chaldea,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["says Jerusalem."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"Therefore this is what the LORD says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Behold, I will plead your case"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and take vengeance on your behalf;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will dry up her sea"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and make her springs run dry."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"Babylon will become a heap of rubble,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a haunt for jackals,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["51:37"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["serpents"]}," or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["dragons"]},""]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["an object of horror and scorn,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["without inhabitant."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"They will roar together like young lions;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they will growl like lion cubs."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"While they are flushed with heat,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will serve them a feast,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and I will make them drunk"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["so that they may revel;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["then they will fall asleep forever and never wake up,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40"},"I will bring them down like lambs to the slaughter,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like rams with male goats."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41"},"How Sheshach",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["51:41"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Sheshach"]}," is a code name for Babylon."]}],"caller":"+"},"has been captured!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The praise of all the earth has been seized."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["What a horror Babylon has become"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["among the nations!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42"},"The sea has come up over Babylon;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["she is covered in turbulent waves."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43"},"Her cities have become a desolation,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a dry and arid land,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["a land where no one lives,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["where no son of man passes through."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44"},"I will punish Bel in Babylon."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will make him spew out what he swallowed."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The nations will no longer stream to him;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["even the wall of Babylon will fall."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45"},"Come out of her, My people!",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["51:45"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["See",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Revelation 18:4"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Save your lives, each of you,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from the fierce anger of the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46"},"Do not let your heart grow faint,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and do not be afraid"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["when the rumor is heard in the land;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for a rumor will come one year—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and then another the next year—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["of violence in the land"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and of ruler against ruler."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47"},"Therefore, behold, the days are coming"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["when I will punish the idols of Babylon."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Her entire land will suffer shame,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and all her slain will lie fallen within her."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48"},"Then heaven and earth and all that is in them"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["will shout for joy over Babylon"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["because the destroyers from the north"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["will come against her,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49"},"“Babylon must fall"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["on account of the slain of Israel,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["just as the slain of all the earth"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["have fallen because of Babylon."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50"},"You who have escaped the sword,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["depart and do not linger!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Remember the LORD from far away,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and let Jerusalem come to mind.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51"},"“We are ashamed because we have heard reproach;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["disgrace has covered our faces,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["because foreigners have entered"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the holy places of the LORD’s house.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"52"},"“Therefore, behold, the days are coming,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["declares the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“when I will punish her idols,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and throughout her land the wounded will groan."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"53"},"Even if Babylon ascends to the heavens"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and fortifies her lofty stronghold,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["the destroyers I send will come against her,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["declares the LORD."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"54"},"“The sound of a cry"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["comes from Babylon,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["the sound of great destruction"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from the land of the Chaldeans!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"55"},"For the LORD will destroy Babylon;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He will silence her mighty voice."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The waves will roar like great waters;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the tumult of their voices will resound."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"56"},"For a destroyer is coming against her—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["against Babylon."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Her warriors will be captured,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and their bows will be broken,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for the LORD is a God of retribution;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He will repay in full."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"57"},"I will make her princes and wise men drunk,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["along with her governors, officials, and warriors."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Then they will fall asleep forever"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and not wake up,”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["declares the King,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["whose name is the LORD of Hosts."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"58"},"This is what the LORD of Hosts says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Babylon’s thick walls will be leveled,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and her high gates consumed by fire."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["So the labor of the people will be for nothing;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the nations will exhaust themselves to fuel the flames.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jeremiah’s Message to Seraiah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"59"},"This is the message that Jeremiah the prophet gave to the quartermaster Seraiah son of Neriah, the son of Mahseiah, when he went to Babylon with King Zedekiah of Judah in the fourth year of Zedekiah’s reign.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"60"},"Jeremiah had written on a single scroll about all the disaster that would come upon Babylon—all these words that had been written concerning Babylon."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"61"},"And Jeremiah said to Seraiah, “When you get to Babylon, see that you read all these words aloud,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"62"},"and say, ‘O LORD, You have promised to cut off this place so that no one will remain—neither man nor beast. Indeed, it will be desolate forever.’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"63"},"When you finish reading this scroll, tie a stone to it and cast it into the Euphrates.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"64"},"Then you are to say, ‘In the same way Babylon will sink and never rise again, because of the disaster I will bring upon her. And her people will grow weary.’”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Here end the words of Jeremiah."]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"52"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Fall of Jerusalem Recounted"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Psalm 74:1–23; Psalm 79:1–13; 2 Kings 24:18–20; 2 Chronicles 36:11–14)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Zedekiah was twenty-one years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem eleven years. His mother’s name was Hamutal daughter of Jeremiah; she was from Libnah."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"And Zedekiah did evil in the sight of the LORD, just as Jehoiakim had done.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"For because of the anger of the LORD, all this happened in Jerusalem and Judah, until He finally banished them from His presence."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["And Zedekiah also rebelled against the king of Babylon."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"So in the ninth year of Zedekiah’s reign, on the tenth day of the tenth month, Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon marched against Jerusalem with his entire army. They encamped outside the city and built a siege wall all around it.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"And the city was kept under siege until King Zedekiah’s eleventh year."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"By the ninth day of the fourth month, the famine in the city was so severe that the people of the land had no food.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Then the city was breached; and though the Chaldeans",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["52:7"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, the Babylonians; similarly in verses 8, 9, 14, and 17"]}],"caller":"+"},"had surrounded the city, all the men of war fled the city by night by way of the gate between the two walls near the king’s garden."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They headed toward the Arabah,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["52:7"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["the Jordan Valley"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"but the army of the Chaldeans pursued the king and overtook Zedekiah in the plains of Jericho, and his whole army deserted him."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"The Chaldeans seized the king and brought him up to the king of Babylon at Riblah in the land of Hamath, where he pronounced judgment on Zedekiah."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"There at Riblah the king of Babylon slaughtered the sons of Zedekiah before his eyes, and he also killed all the officials of Judah.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Then he put out Zedekiah’s eyes, bound him with bronze shackles, and took him to Babylon, where he kept him in custody until his dying day."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Temple Destroyed"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(2 Kings 25:8–17)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"On the tenth day of the fifth month, in the nineteenth year of Nebuchadnezzar’s reign over Babylon, Nebuzaradan captain of the guard, a servant of the king of Babylon, entered Jerusalem.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"He burned down the house of the LORD, the royal palace, and all the houses of Jerusalem—every significant building.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"And the whole army of the Chaldeans under the captain of the guard broke down all the walls around Jerusalem."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Then Nebuzaradan captain of the guard carried into exile some of the poorest people and those who remained in the city, along with the deserters who had defected to the king of Babylon and the rest of the craftsmen.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"But Nebuzaradan captain of the guard left behind some of the poorest of the land to tend the vineyards and fields."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Moreover, the Chaldeans broke up the bronze pillars and stands and the bronze Sea in the house of the LORD, and they carried all the bronze to Babylon.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"They also took away the pots, shovels, wick trimmers, sprinkling bowls, dishes, and all the articles of bronze used in the temple service.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"The captain of the guard also took away the basins, censers, sprinkling bowls, pots, lampstands, pans, and drink offering bowls—anything made of pure gold or fine silver."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"As for the two pillars, the Sea, the twelve bronze bulls under it, and the movable stands that King Solomon had made for the house of the LORD, the weight of the bronze from all these articles was beyond measure.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Each pillar was eighteen cubits tall and twelve cubits in circumference;",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["52:21"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Each pillar was approximately 27 feet high and 18 feet in circumference (8.2 meters high and 5.5 meters in circumference)."]}],"caller":"+"},"each was hollow, four fingers thick.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["52:21"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["4 fingers"]}," is approximately 2.9 inches or 7.4 centimeters."]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"The bronze capital atop one pillar was five cubits high,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["52:22"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["5 cubits"]}," is approximately 7.5 feet or 2.3 meters."]}],"caller":"+"},"with a network of bronze pomegranates all around. The second pillar, with its pomegranates, was similar.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Each capital had ninety-six pomegranates on the sides, and a total of a hundred pomegranates were above the surrounding network."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Captives Carried to Babylon"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(2 Kings 25:18–21)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"The captain of the guard also took away Seraiah the chief priest, Zephaniah the priest of second rank, and the three doorkeepers.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"Of those still in the city, he took a court official who had been appointed over the men of war, as well as seven trusted royal advisers. He also took the scribe of the captain of the army, who had enlisted the people of the land, and sixty men who were found in the city."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"Nebuzaradan captain of the guard took them and brought them to the king of Babylon at Riblah.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"There at Riblah in the land of Hamath, the king of Babylon struck them down and put them to death. So Judah was taken into exile, away from its own land."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"These are the people Nebuchadnezzar carried away:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"li1","content":["in the seventh year, 3,023 Jews;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"li1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"in Nebuchadnezzar’s eighteenth year, 832 people from Jerusalem;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"li1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"in Nebuchadnezzar’s twenty-third year, Nebuzaradan captain of the guard carried away 745 Jews."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["So in all, 4,600 people were taken away."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jehoiachin Released from Prison"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(2 Kings 25:27–30)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"On the twenty-fifth day of the twelfth month of the thirty-seventh year of the exile of Jehoiachin king of Judah, in the first year of the reign of Evil-merodach king of Babylon, he pardoned",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["52:31"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["he lifted up the head of"]},""]}],"caller":"+"},"Jehoiachin king of Judah and released him from prison.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"And he spoke kindly to Jehoiachin and set his throne above the thrones of the other kings who were with him in Babylon."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"So Jehoiachin changed out of his prison clothes, and he dined regularly at the king’s table for the rest of his life.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"And the king of Babylon provided Jehoiachin a daily portion for the rest of his life, until the day of his death."]}]}